\mt1 Isaiah
\c 1
\p
\v 1 The \x + \xo 1:1 \xt ch. 6:1 \x*vision of Isaiah the son of Amoz, which he saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem \x + \xo 1:1 \xt Hos. 1:1; Mic. 1:1 \x*in the days of \x + \xo 1:1 \xt [2 Kgs. 15:1, 7]; See 2 Chr. 26 \x*Uzziah, \x + \xo 1:1 \xt See 2 Kgs. 15:32-38; 2 Chr. 27 \x*Jotham, \x + \xo 1:1 \xt ch. 7:1, 3, 10, 12; 14:28; See 2 Kgs. 16; 2 Chr. 28 \x*Ahaz, and \x + \xo 1:1 \xt See ch. 37:2–39:8; 2 Kgs. 18-20; 2 Chr. 29–32\x*Hezekiah, kings of Judah.
\s1 The Wickedness of Judah
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 1:2 \xt Deut. 32:1; [Deut. 4:26] \x*Hear, O heavens, and give ear, O \x + \xo 1:2 \xt Mic. 1:2; 6:2 \x*earth;
\q2 for the \nd Lord\nd* has spoken:
\q1 “Children\f + \fr 1:2 \ft Or \fq Sons\ft ; also verse 4\f* \x + \xo 1:2 \xt [Deut. 32:6, 10, 15]\x*have I reared and brought up,
\q2 but they have rebelled against me.
\q1
\v 3 The ox \x + \xo 1:3 \xt [Jer. 8:7]\x*knows its owner,
\q2 and the donkey its master’s crib,
\q1 but Israel does \x + \xo 1:3 \xt [Jer. 8:7]\x*not know,
\q2 my people do not understand.”
\b
\q1
\v 4 Ah, sinful nation,
\q2 a people laden with iniquity,
\q1 \x + \xo 1:4 \xt [Matt. 3:7] \x*offspring of evildoers,
\q2 children who deal corruptly!
\q1 They have forsaken the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 they have \x + \xo 1:4 \xt ch. 5:24 \x*despised \x + \xo 1:4 \xt See ch. 31:1 \x*the Holy One of Israel,
\q2 they are utterly \x + \xo 1:4 \xt Ezek. 14:5\x*estranged.
\b
\q1
\v 5 Why will you still be \x + \xo 1:5 \xt Jer. 5:3; [ch. 9:13] \x*struck down?
\q2 Why will you \x + \xo 1:5 \xt ch. 31:6\x*continue to rebel?
\q1 The whole head is sick,
\q2 and the whole heart faint.
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 1:6 \xt Ps. 38:3 \x*From the sole of the foot even to the head,
\q2 there is no soundness in it,
\q1 but bruises and sores
\q2 and raw wounds;
\q1 they are \x + \xo 1:6 \xt [Jer. 8:22]\x*not pressed out or bound up
\q2 or softened with oil.
\b
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 1:7 \xt ch. 5:5; 6:11, 12; Deut. 28:51, 52\x*Your country lies desolate;
\q2 your cities are burned with fire;
\q1 in your very presence
\q2 foreigners devour your land;
\q2 it is desolate, as overthrown by foreigners.
\q1
\v 8 And \x + \xo 1:8 \xt ch. 10:32; 37:22; Zech. 2:10; 9:9 \x*the daughter of Zion is left
\q2 like a \x + \xo 1:8 \xt Job 27:18\x*booth in a vineyard,
\q1 like a lodge in a cucumber field,
\q2 like a besieged city.
\b
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 1:9 \xt Lam. 3:22 \x*If the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts
\q2 had not left us \x + \xo 1:9 \xt ch. 10:21, 22; Cited Rom. 9:29 \x*a few survivors,
\q1 we should have been like \x + \xo 1:9 \xt ch. 13:19; Gen. 19:24, 25\x*Sodom,
\q2 and become like \x + \xo 1:9 \xt ch. 13:19; Gen. 19:24, 25\x*Gomorrah.
\b
\q1
\v 10 Hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 you rulers of \x + \xo 1:10 \xt Ezek. 16:46, 48, 49, 55; [ch. 3:9; Rev. 11:8] \x*\x + \xo 1:10 \xt [Deut. 32:32]\x*Sodom!
\q1 Give ear to the teaching\f + \fr 1:10 \ft Or \fq law\f* of our God,
\q2 you people of \x + \xo 1:10 \xt [Deut. 32:32]\x*Gomorrah!
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 1:11 \xt Prov. 15:8; Jer. 6:20; Mal. 1:10; [ch. 66:3]; See 1 Sam. 15:22\x*“What to me is the multitude of your sacrifices?
\q2 says the \nd Lord\nd*;
\q1 I have had enough of burnt offerings of rams
\q2 and the fat of well-fed beasts;
\q1 I do not delight in the blood of bulls,
\q2 or of lambs, or of goats.
\b
\q1
\v 12 “When you come to \x + \xo 1:12 \xt Ex. 23:17; 34:23\x*appear before me,
\q2 who has required of you
\q2 this trampling of my courts?
\q1
\v 13 Bring no more vain offerings;
\q2 incense is an abomination to me.
\q1 \x + \xo 1:13 \xt Num. 28:11; 1 Chr. 23:31 \x*New moon and Sabbath and the \x + \xo 1:13 \xt Ex. 12:16; Lev. 23:36 \x*calling of convocations—
\q2 I cannot endure \x + \xo 1:13 \xt [Jer. 7:9, 10] \x*iniquity and \x + \xo 1:13 \xt See Joel 2:15-17\x*solemn assembly.
\q1
\v 14 Your \x + \xo 1:14 \xt [See ver. 13 above]\x*new moons and your appointed feasts
\q2 my soul hates;
\q1 they have become a burden to me;
\q2 I am weary of bearing them.
\q1
\v 15 When you \x + \xo 1:15 \xt 1 Kgs. 8:22 \x*spread out your hands,
\q2 I will hide my eyes from you;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:15 \xt Prov. 1:28; Mic. 3:4 \x*even though you make many prayers,
\q2 I will not listen;
\q2 \x + \xo 1:15 \xt ch. 59:3\x*your hands are full of blood.
\q1
\v 16 \x + \xo 1:16 \xt [Jer. 2:22] \x*Wash yourselves; make yourselves clean;
\q2 remove the evil of your deeds from before my eyes;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:16 \xt [1 Pet. 3:11]\x*cease to do evil,
\q2
\v 17 learn to do good;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:17 \xt Jer. 22:3 \x*seek justice,
\q2 correct oppression;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:17 \xt [ver. 23; James 1:27]\x*bring justice to the fatherless,
\q2 plead the widow’s cause.
\b
\q1
\v 18 “Come now, \x + \xo 1:18 \xt Mic. 6:2; [ch. 43:26] \x*let us reason\f + \fr 1:18 \ft Or \fq dispute\f* together, says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\q1 though your sins are like scarlet,
\q2 they shall be as \x + \xo 1:18 \xt Ps. 51:7; [Rev. 7:14]\x*white as snow;
\q1 though they are red like crimson,
\q2 they shall become like wool.
\q1
\v 19 \x + \xo 1:19 \xt Deut. 30:15, 16\x*If you are willing and obedient,
\q2 you shall eat the good of the land;
\q1
\v 20 but if you refuse and rebel,
\q2 you shall be eaten by the sword;
\q2 \x + \xo 1:20 \xt ver. 2; ch. 24:3; 40:5; 58:14; Mic. 4:4; [Num. 23:19]\x*for the mouth of the \nd Lord\nd* has spoken.”
\s1 The Unfaithful City
\q1
\v 21 How the faithful city
\q2 \x + \xo 1:21 \xt Jer. 2:20; [Ex. 34:15] \x*has become a whore,\f + \fr 1:21 \ft Or \fq become unchaste\f*
\q2 \x + \xo 1:21 \xt [Jer. 31:23]\x*she who was full of justice!
\q1 Righteousness lodged in her,
\q2 but now murderers.
\q1
\v 22 \x + \xo 1:22 \xt [Jer. 6:30; Ezek. 22:18]\x*Your silver has become dross,
\q2 your best wine mixed with water.
\q1
\v 23 Your princes are rebels
\q2 and companions of thieves.
\q1 Everyone \x + \xo 1:23 \xt Mic. 7:3; [Ex. 23:8] \x*loves a bribe
\q2 and runs after gifts.
\q1 \x + \xo 1:23 \xt Jer. 5:28; Zech. 7:10; [ver. 17]\x*They do not bring justice to the fatherless,
\q2 and the widow’s cause does not come to them.
\b
\q1
\v 24 Therefore the \x + \xo 1:24 \xt ch. 3:1; 10:33 \x*Lord declares,
\q2 the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts,
\q2 the \x + \xo 1:24 \xt Ps. 132:2 \x*Mighty One of Israel:
\q1 “Ah, I will get relief from my enemies
\q2 \x + \xo 1:24 \xt [Deut. 32:41]\x*and avenge myself on my foes.
\q1
\v 25 \x + \xo 1:25 \xt Ps. 81:14; Amos 1:8; [ch. 5:25] \x*I will turn my hand against you
\q2 and will smelt away your \x + \xo 1:25 \xt [Ezek. 22:20; Mal. 3:3]\x*dross as with lye
\q2 and remove all your alloy.
\q1
\v 26 And I will restore your judges \x + \xo 1:26 \xt Jer. 33:7, 11 \x*as at the first,
\q2 and your counselors as at the beginning.
\q1 Afterward \x + \xo 1:26 \xt [Zech. 8:3]\x*you shall be called the city of righteousness,
\q2 the faithful city.”
\b
\q1
\v 27 \x + \xo 1:27 \xt Jer. 22:3, 4\x*Zion shall be redeemed by justice,
\q2 and those in her who repent, by righteousness.
\q1
\v 28 \x + \xo 1:28 \xt Job 31:3; Ps. 1:6\x*But rebels and sinners shall be broken together,
\q2 and those who forsake the \nd Lord\nd* shall be consumed.
\q1
\v 29 \x + \xo 1:29 \xt Hos. 4:19 \x*For they\f + \fr 1:29 \ft Some Hebrew manuscripts \fq you\f* shall be ashamed of \x + \xo 1:29 \xt ch. 57:5; Hos. 4:13 \x*the oaks
\q2 that you desired;
\q1 and you shall blush for \x + \xo 1:29 \xt ch. 65:3; 66:17\x*the gardens
\q2 that you have chosen.
\q1
\v 30 For you shall be \x + \xo 1:30 \xt [Jer. 17:8]\x*like an oak
\q2 whose leaf withers,
\q2 and like a garden without water.
\q1
\v 31 And the strong shall become \x + \xo 1:31 \xt Judg. 16:9 \x*tinder,
\q2 and his work a spark,
\q1 and both of them shall burn together,
\q2 with \x + \xo 1:31 \xt ch. 66:24\x*none to quench them.
\c 2
\s1 The Mountain of the \nd Lord\nd*
\p
\v 1 The word that Isaiah the son of Amoz saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem.
\b
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 2:2 \xt For ver. 2-4, see Mic. 4:1-3 \x*It shall come to pass in the latter days
\q2 that \x + \xo 2:2 \xt ch. 14:13; 25:6 \x*the mountain of the house of the \nd Lord\nd*
\q1 shall be established as the highest of the mountains,
\q2 and shall be lifted up above the hills;
\q1 and \x + \xo 2:2 \xt [ch. 56:7]\x*all the nations shall flow to it,
\q2
\v 3 and \x + \xo 2:3 \xt See Zech. 8:20-23 \x*many peoples shall come, and say:
\q1 “Come, let us go up to the mountain of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 to the house of the God of Jacob,
\q1 that he may teach us his ways
\q2 and that we may walk in his paths.”
\q1 For \x + \xo 2:3 \xt [Luke 24:47; John 4:22]\x*out of Zion shall go the law,\f + \fr 2:3 \ft Or \fq teaching\f*
\q2 and the word of the \nd Lord\nd* from Jerusalem.
\q1
\v 4 He shall judge between the nations,
\q2 and shall decide disputes for many peoples;
\q1 \x + \xo 2:4 \xt [Joel 3:10] \x*and they shall beat their swords into plowshares,
\q2 and their spears into pruning hooks;
\q1 \x + \xo 2:4 \xt ch. 9:7; Ps. 72:3, 7; Hos. 2:18; Zech. 9:10\x*nation shall not lift up sword against nation,
\q2 neither shall they learn war anymore.
\b
\q1
\v 5 O house of Jacob,
\q2 come, let us walk
\q2 in \x + \xo 2:5 \xt ch. 60:1, 2; [Eph. 5:8]\x*the light of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\s1 The Day of the \nd Lord\nd*
\q1
\v 6 For you have rejected your people,
\q2 the house of Jacob,
\q1 because they are full of things \x + \xo 2:6 \xt [2 Kgs. 16:10, 11] \x*from the east
\q2 and \x + \xo 2:6 \xt Mic. 5:12 \x*of fortune-tellers \x + \xo 2:6 \xt 2 Kgs. 1:2 \x*like the Philistines,
\q2 and they \x + \xo 2:6 \xt [2 Kgs. 16:7, 8]\x*strike hands with the children of foreigners.
\q1
\v 7 Their land is \x + \xo 2:7 \xt ch. 39:2; [ch. 22:8, 11; Deut. 17:17] \x*filled with silver and gold,
\q2 and there is no end to their treasures;
\q1 their land is \x + \xo 2:7 \xt ch. 30:16; [Deut. 17:16; Mic. 5:10]\x*filled with horses,
\q2 and there is no end to their chariots.
\q1
\v 8 Their land is \x + \xo 2:8 \xt ver. 18, 20; ch. 10:10, 11; Jer. 2:28 \x*filled with idols;
\q2 they bow down to \x + \xo 2:8 \xt See ch. 44:9-17\x*the work of their hands,
\q2 to what their own fingers have made.
\q1
\v 9 So man \x + \xo 2:9 \xt ch. 5:15\x*is humbled,
\q2 and each one \x + \xo 2:9 \xt ch. 5:15\x*is brought low—
\q2 do not forgive them!
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 2:10 \xt ver. 19, 21; [Rev. 6:15, 16] \x*Enter into the rock
\q2 and hide in the dust
\q1 \x + \xo 2:10 \xt Cited 2 Thess. 1:9\x*from before the terror of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and from the splendor of his majesty.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 2:11 \xt ver. 17; Ps. 18:27; [Mic. 2:3; 2 Cor. 10:5]\x*The haughty looks of man shall be brought low,
\q2 and the lofty pride of men shall be humbled,
\q1 and the \nd Lord\nd* alone will be exalted in that day.
\b
\q1
\v 12 \x + \xo 2:12 \xt [Job 40:11, 12; Mal. 4:1]\x*For the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts has a day
\q2 against all that is proud and lofty,
\q2 against all that is lifted up—and it shall be brought low;
\q1
\v 13 against all the \x + \xo 2:13 \xt ch. 14:8; See Judg. 9:15 \x*cedars of Lebanon,
\q2 lofty and lifted up;
\q2 and against all the \x + \xo 2:13 \xt Ezek. 27:6; Zech. 11:2\x*oaks of Bashan;
\q1
\v 14 against all \x + \xo 2:14 \xt [ch. 30:25]\x*the lofty mountains,
\q2 and against all the uplifted hills;
\q1
\v 15 against every high tower,
\q2 and against every fortified wall;
\q1
\v 16 against all \x + \xo 2:16 \xt ch. 60:9; 1 Kgs. 10:22\x*the ships of Tarshish,
\q2 and against all the beautiful craft.
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 2:17 \xt Ps. 18:27; [Mic. 2:3; 2 Cor. 10:5]\x*And the haughtiness of man shall be humbled,
\q2 and the lofty pride of men shall be brought low,
\q2 and the \nd Lord\nd* alone will be exalted in that day.
\q1
\v 18 \x + \xo 2:18 \xt ver. 8\x*And the idols shall utterly pass away.
\q1
\v 19 \x + \xo 2:19 \xt ver. 10; Hos. 10:8; Luke 23:30; Rev. 6:16 \x*And people shall enter the caves of the rocks
\q2 and the holes of the ground,\f + \fr 2:19 \ft Hebrew \fq dust\f*
\q1 from before the terror of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and from the splendor of his majesty,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:19 \xt [Ps. 76:8, 9; Hab. 3:6]\x*when he rises to terrify the earth.
\b
\q1
\v 20 In that day \x + \xo 2:20 \xt ch. 30:22; 31:7 \x*mankind will cast away
\q2 their idols of silver and their idols of gold,
\q1 which they made for themselves to worship,
\q2 to the moles and to the \x + \xo 2:20 \xt Lev. 11:19; Deut. 14:18\x*bats,
\q1
\v 21 \x + \xo 2:21 \xt [See ver. 19 above] \x*to enter the caverns of the rocks
\q2 and the clefts of the cliffs,
\q1 from before the terror of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and from the splendor of his majesty,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:21 \xt [See ver. 19 above]\x*when he rises to terrify the earth.
\q1
\v 22 \x + \xo 2:22 \xt Ps. 146:3 \x*Stop regarding man
\q2 \x + \xo 2:22 \xt Job 27:3; [James 4:14]\x*in whose nostrils is breath,
\q2 for of what account is he?
\c 3
\s1 Judgment on Judah and Jerusalem
\q1
\v 1 For behold, the \x + \xo 3:1 \xt ch. 1:24 \x*Lord \nd God\nd* of hosts
\q2 is taking away from Jerusalem and from Judah
\q1 support and supply,\f + \fr 3:1 \ft Hebrew \fq staff\f*
\q2 all \x + \xo 3:1 \xt Lev. 26:26; Ezek. 4:16\x*support of bread,
\q2 and all support of water;
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 3:2 \xt 2 Kgs. 24:14; Ezek. 17:13, 14\x*the mighty man and the soldier,
\q2 the judge and the prophet,
\q2 the diviner and the elder,
\q1
\v 3 the captain of fifty
\q2 and the man of rank,
\q1 the counselor and the skillful magician
\q2 and the expert in charms.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 3:4 \xt ver. 12; Eccles. 10:16\x*And I will make boys their princes,
\q2 and infants\f + \fr 3:4 \ft Or \fq caprice\f* shall rule over them.
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 3:5 \xt See Mic. 7:3-6\x*And the people will oppress one another,
\q2 every one his fellow
\q2 and every one his neighbor;
\q1 the youth will be insolent to the elder,
\q2 and the despised to the honorable.
\b
\q1
\v 6 For \x + \xo 3:6 \xt ch. 4:1\x*a man will take hold of his brother
\q2 in the house of his father, saying:
\q1 “You have a cloak;
\q2 you shall be our leader,
\q1 and this heap of ruins
\q2 shall be under your rule”;
\q1
\v 7 in that day he will speak out, saying:
\q1 “I will not be a \x + \xo 3:7 \xt [ch. 1:6]\x*healer;\f + \fr 3:7 \ft Hebrew \fq binder of wounds\f*
\q2 in my house there is neither bread nor cloak;
\q1 you shall not make me
\q2 leader of the people.”
\q1
\v 8 For Jerusalem has stumbled,
\q2 and Judah has fallen,
\q1 because their \x + \xo 3:8 \xt See Ps. 73:9-11 \x*speech and their deeds are against the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:8 \xt ch. 65:3\x*defying his glorious presence.\f + \fr 3:8 \ft Hebrew \fq the eyes of his glory\f*
\b
\q1
\v 9 For the look on their faces bears witness against them;
\q2 they proclaim their sin \x + \xo 3:9 \xt Gen. 13:13; 18:20; Ezek. 16:46, 48, 49 \x*like Sodom;
\q2 they do not hide it.
\q1 Woe to them!
\q2 \x + \xo 3:9 \xt [Rom. 6:23]\x*For they have brought evil on themselves.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 3:10 \xt Eccles. 8:12; See Deut. 28:1-14 \x*Tell the righteous that it shall be well with them,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:10 \xt Ps. 128:2\x*for they shall eat the fruit of their deeds.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 3:11 \xt Eccles. 8:13; See Deut. 28:15-68\x*Woe to the wicked! It shall be ill with him,
\q2 for what his hands have dealt out shall be done to him.
\q1
\v 12 My people—\x + \xo 3:12 \xt ver. 4 \x*infants are their oppressors,
\q2 and women rule over them.
\q1 O my people, \x + \xo 3:12 \xt See ch. 28:14-22\x*your guides mislead you
\q2 and they have swallowed up\f + \fr 3:12 \ft Or \fq they have confused\f* the course of your paths.
\b
\q1
\v 13 The \nd Lord\nd* \x + \xo 3:13 \xt Ps. 7:6; Hos. 4:1\x*has taken his place to contend;
\q2 he stands to judge peoples.
\q1
\v 14 The \nd Lord\nd* will enter into judgment
\q2 with the \x + \xo 3:14 \xt Mic. 3:1 \x*elders and princes of his people:
\q1 “It is you who \x + \xo 3:14 \xt Ps. 14:4 \x*have devoured\f + \fr 3:14 \ft Or \fq grazed over\ft ; compare Exodus 22:5\f* the vineyard,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:14 \xt Amos 3:10\x*the spoil of the poor is in your houses.
\q1
\v 15 What do you mean by \x + \xo 3:15 \xt [Ps. 94:5]\x*crushing my people,
\q2 by grinding the face of the poor?”
\qr declares the Lord \nd God\nd* of hosts.
\b
\q1
\v 16 The \nd Lord\nd* said:
\q1 \x + \xo 3:16 \xt See ch. 32:9-11 \x*Because \x + \xo 3:16 \xt ch. 4:4; Song 3:11 \x*the daughters of Zion are haughty
\q2 and walk with outstretched necks,
\q2 glancing wantonly with their eyes,
\q1 mincing along as they go,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:16 \xt ver. 18\x*tinkling with their feet,
\q1
\v 17 therefore the Lord \x + \xo 3:17 \xt [Deut. 28:60] \x*will strike with a scab
\q2 the heads of \x + \xo 3:17 \xt [See ver. 16 above]\x*the daughters of Zion,
\q2 and the \nd Lord\nd* will lay bare their secret parts.
\b
\p
\v 18 In that day the Lord will take away \x + \xo 3:18 \xt ver. 16 \x*the finery of the anklets, the \x + \xo 3:18 \xt [1 Pet. 3:3] \x*headbands, and the \x + \xo 3:18 \xt Judg. 8:21, 26\x*crescents;
\v 19 the pendants, the bracelets, and the scarves;
\v 20 the \x + \xo 3:20 \xt Ex. 39:28; Ezek. 24:17\x*headdresses, the armlets, the sashes, the perfume boxes, and the amulets;
\v 21 the signet rings and \x + \xo 3:21 \xt Gen. 24:47; Ezek. 16:12\x*nose rings;
\v 22 the \x + \xo 3:22 \xt [Luke 15:22]\x*festal robes, the mantles, the cloaks, and the handbags;
\v 23 the mirrors, the linen garments, the turbans, and the veils.
\b
\q1
\v 24 Instead of \x + \xo 3:24 \xt [Esth. 2:12] \x*perfume there will be rottenness;
\q2 and instead of a \x + \xo 3:24 \xt Prov. 31:24 \x*belt, a rope;
\q1 and instead of \x + \xo 3:24 \xt 1 Pet. 3:3 \x*well-set hair, \x + \xo 3:24 \xt ch. 15:2; 22:12; Ezek. 27:31; Amos 8:10; Mic. 1:16 \x*baldness;
\q2 and instead of a rich robe, a \x + \xo 3:24 \xt ch. 15:3; Gen. 37:34; Lam. 2:10 \x*skirt of sackcloth;
\q2 and \x + \xo 3:24 \xt Lev. 19:28\x*branding instead of beauty.
\q1
\v 25 Your men shall fall by the sword
\q2 and your mighty men in battle.
\q1
\v 26 And \x + \xo 3:26 \xt Jer. 14:2; Lam. 1:4 \x*her gates shall lament and mourn;
\q2 empty, she shall \x + \xo 3:26 \xt Job 2:13; Lam. 2:10\x*sit on the ground.
\b
\c 4
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 4:1 \xt [ch. 13:12] \x*And seven women \x + \xo 4:1 \xt ch. 3:6 \x*shall take hold of \x + \xo 4:1 \xt [ch. 13:12] \x*one man in that day, saying, “We will eat our own bread and wear our own clothes, only let us be called by your name; \x + \xo 4:1 \xt See Gen. 30:23\x*take away our reproach.”
\s1 The Branch of the \nd Lord\nd* Glorified
\p
\v 2 In that day \x + \xo 4:2 \xt Jer. 23:5; 33:15; Zech. 3:8; 6:12 \x*the branch of the \nd Lord\nd* shall be beautiful and glorious, and \x + \xo 4:2 \xt [ch. 27:6]\x*the fruit of the land shall be the pride and honor of the survivors of Israel.
\v 3 \x + \xo 4:3 \xt ch. 6:13; 10:20 \x*And he who is left in Zion and remains in Jerusalem will be called \x + \xo 4:3 \xt Obad. 17 \x*holy, everyone who has \x + \xo 4:3 \xt Ex. 32:32; Luke 10:20; Heb. 12:23; [Ps. 69:28]\x*been recorded for life in Jerusalem,
\v 4 when \x + \xo 4:4 \xt Ezek. 36:25 \x*the Lord shall have washed away the filth of \x + \xo 4:4 \xt ch. 3:16 \x*the daughters of Zion and cleansed the bloodstains of Jerusalem from its midst by a spirit of judgment and by \x + \xo 4:4 \xt ch. 33:14; Mal. 3:2; Matt. 3:11; Luke 3:17\x*a spirit of burning.\f + \fr 4:4 \ft Or \fq purging\f*
\v 5 Then the \nd Lord\nd* will create over the whole site of Mount Zion and over her assemblies \x + \xo 4:5 \xt Ex. 13:21 \x*a cloud by day, and smoke and the shining of a flaming fire by night; for over all the glory there will be \x + \xo 4:5 \xt [Rev. 7:15]\x*a canopy.
\v 6 \x + \xo 4:6 \xt ch. 25:4 \x*There will be a \x + \xo 4:6 \xt See Ps. 27:5 \x*booth for shade by day from the heat, and \x + \xo 4:6 \xt ch. 25:4\x*for a refuge and a shelter from the storm and rain.
\c 5
\s1 The Vineyard of the \nd Lord\nd* Destroyed
\q1
\v 1 Let me sing for my beloved
\q2 my love song concerning his vineyard:
\q1 My beloved had \x + \xo 5:1 \xt Ps. 80:8; Matt. 21:33; Mark 12:1; Luke 20:9; [Hos. 9:10]\x*a vineyard
\q2 on a very fertile hill.
\q1
\v 2 He dug it and cleared it of stones,
\q2 and planted it with \x + \xo 5:2 \xt Jer. 2:21 \x*choice vines;
\q1 he built a watchtower in the midst of it,
\q2 and hewed out a wine vat in it;
\q1 and \x + \xo 5:2 \xt [Matt. 21:19; Mark 11:13; Luke 13:6]\x*he looked for it to yield grapes,
\q2 but it yielded wild grapes.
\b
\q1
\v 3 And now, O inhabitants of Jerusalem
\q2 and men of Judah,
\q1 judge between me and my vineyard.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 5:4 \xt [Mic. 6:3, 4] \x*What more was there to do for my vineyard,
\q2 that I have not done in it?
\q1 \x + \xo 5:4 \xt [See ver. 2 above]\x*When I looked for it to yield grapes,
\q2 why did it yield wild grapes?
\b
\q1
\v 5 And now I will tell you
\q2 what I will do to my vineyard.
\q1 I will remove \x + \xo 5:5 \xt [Jer. 5:10] \x*its hedge,
\q2 and it shall be devoured;\f + \fr 5:5 \ft Or \fq grazed over\ft ; compare Exodus 22:5\f*
\q1 \x + \xo 5:5 \xt Ps. 80:12; [Prov. 24:31]\x*I will break down its wall,
\q2 and it shall be trampled down.
\q1
\v 6 I will make it a waste;
\q2 it shall not be pruned or hoed,
\q2 and \x + \xo 5:6 \xt See ch. 7:23-25 \x*briers and thorns shall grow up;
\q1 \x + \xo 5:6 \xt [1 Kgs. 17:1; Jer. 14:1, 22]\x*I will also command the clouds
\q2 that they rain no rain upon it.
\b
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 5:7 \xt [ch. 3:14]; See Ps. 80:8-11\x*For the vineyard of the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts
\q2 is the house of Israel,
\q1 and the men of Judah
\q2 are his pleasant planting;
\q1 and he looked for justice,
\q2 but behold, bloodshed;\f + \fr 5:7 \ft The Hebrew words for \fq justice \ft and \fq bloodshed \ft sound alike\f*
\q1 for righteousness,
\q2 but behold, an outcry!\f + \fr 5:7 \ft The Hebrew words for \fq righteous \ft and \fq outcry \ft sound alike\f*
\s1 Woe to the Wicked
\q1
\v 8 Woe to those who \x + \xo 5:8 \xt Mic. 2:2\x*join house to house,
\q2 who add field to field,
\q1 until there is no more room,
\q2 and you are made to dwell alone
\q2 in the midst of the land.
\q1
\v 9 The \nd Lord\nd* of hosts has sworn in my hearing:
\q1 \x + \xo 5:9 \xt ch. 6:12\x*“Surely many houses shall be desolate,
\q2 large and beautiful houses, without inhabitant.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 5:10 \xt [Lev. 26:26; Hag. 1:6; 2:16] \x*For ten acres\f + \fr 5:10 \ft Hebrew \fq ten yoke\ft , the area ten yoke of oxen can plow in a day\f* of vineyard shall yield but one bath,
\q2 and a \x + \xo 5:10 \xt Ezek. 45:11\x*homer of seed shall yield but an ephah.”\f + \fr 5:10 \ft A \fq bath \ft was about 6 gallons or 22 liters; a \fq homer \ft was about 6 bushels or 220 liters; an \fq ephah \ft was about 3/5 bushel or 22 liters\f*
\b
\q1
\v 11 Woe to those who \x + \xo 5:11 \xt ver. 22; [Prov. 23:29, 30; Eccles. 10:16, 17]\x*rise early in the morning,
\q2 that they may run after strong drink,
\q1 who tarry late into the evening
\q2 as wine inflames them!
\q1
\v 12 \x + \xo 5:12 \xt Amos 6:5, 6 \x*They have lyre and harp,
\q2 tambourine and flute and wine at their feasts,
\q1 \x + \xo 5:12 \xt ch. 26:11\x*but they do not regard the deeds of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 or see the work of his hands.
\b
\q1
\v 13 Therefore my people go into exile
\q2 \x + \xo 5:13 \xt ch. 1:3; Hos. 4:6 \x*for lack of knowledge;\f + \fr 5:13 \ft Or \fq without their knowledge\f*
\q1 their \x + \xo 5:13 \xt [Lam. 4:2, 7, 8]\x*honored men go hungry,\f + \fr 5:13 \ft Or \fq die of hunger\f*
\q2 and their multitude is parched with thirst.
\q1
\v 14 Therefore Sheol has \x + \xo 5:14 \xt Hab. 2:5 \x*enlarged its appetite
\q2 and opened \x + \xo 5:14 \xt Ps. 141:7 \x*its mouth beyond measure,
\q1 and the nobility of Jerusalem\f + \fr 5:14 \ft Hebrew \fq her nobility\f* and her multitude will go down,
\q2 her revelers and he who \x + \xo 5:14 \xt [ver. 12; Job 1:18, 19]\x*exults in her.
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 5:15 \xt ch. 2:9\x*Man is humbled, and each one is brought low,
\q2 and the eyes of the haughty\f + \fr 5:15 \ft Hebrew \fq high\f* are brought low.
\q1
\v 16 \x + \xo 5:16 \xt ch. 2:11, 17\x*But the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts is exalted\f + \fr 5:16 \ft Hebrew \fq high\f* in justice,
\q2 and the Holy God shows himself holy in righteousness.
\q1
\v 17 Then shall the lambs graze \x + \xo 5:17 \xt Mic. 2:12 \x*as in their pasture,
\q2 and \x + \xo 5:17 \xt [Judg. 6:3]\x*nomads shall eat among the ruins of the rich.
\b
\q1
\v 18 Woe to those who draw iniquity with \x + \xo 5:18 \xt Prov. 5:22\x*cords of falsehood,
\q2 who draw sin as with cart ropes,
\q1
\v 19 who say: \x + \xo 5:19 \xt [Ezek. 12:22; 2 Pet. 3:4]\x*“Let him be quick,
\q2 let him speed his work
\q2 that we may see it;
\q1 let the counsel of the Holy One of Israel draw near,
\q2 and let it come, that we may know it!”
\q1
\v 20 Woe to \x + \xo 5:20 \xt [Amos 5:7] \x*those who call evil good
\q2 and good evil,
\q1 \x + \xo 5:20 \xt [Job 17:12; Matt. 6:22, 23; Luke 11:34, 35]\x*who put darkness for light
\q2 and light for darkness,
\q1 who put bitter for sweet
\q2 and sweet for bitter!
\q1
\v 21 Woe to those who are \x + \xo 5:21 \xt Prov. 3:7; Rom. 12:16\x*wise in their own eyes,
\q2 and shrewd in their own sight!
\q1
\v 22 Woe to those who are \x + \xo 5:22 \xt ver. 11\x*heroes at drinking wine,
\q2 and valiant men in mixing strong drink,
\q1
\v 23 who \x + \xo 5:23 \xt Ex. 23:8; Prov. 17:15\x*acquit the guilty for a bribe,
\q2 and deprive the innocent of his right!
\b
\q1
\v 24 Therefore, \x + \xo 5:24 \xt ch. 47:14; Joel 2:5; [Ex. 15:7] \x*as the tongue of fire devours the stubble,
\q2 and as dry grass sinks down in the flame,
\q1 so \x + \xo 5:24 \xt Job 18:16 \x*their root will be \x + \xo 5:24 \xt Hos. 5:12 \x*as rottenness,
\q2 and their blossom go up like dust;
\q1 for they have \x + \xo 5:24 \xt ch. 30:9 \x*rejected the law of the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts,
\q2 and have \x + \xo 5:24 \xt ch. 1:4\x*despised the word of the Holy One of Israel.
\q1
\v 25 Therefore \x + \xo 5:25 \xt 2 Kgs. 22:13, 17 \x*the anger of the \nd Lord\nd* was kindled against his people,
\q2 and he stretched out his hand against them and struck them,
\q2 and \x + \xo 5:25 \xt Jer. 4:24; [Ps. 97:5; Hab. 3:6] \x*the mountains quaked;
\q1 and their corpses were \x + \xo 5:25 \xt [2 Kgs. 9:37; Jer. 36:30] \x*as refuse
\q2 in the midst of the streets.
\q1 \x + \xo 5:25 \xt ch. 9:12, 17, 21; 10:4\x*For all this his anger has not turned away,
\q2 and his hand is stretched out still.
\b
\q1
\v 26 He will \x + \xo 5:26 \xt ch. 11:12; 13:2; 18:3 \x*raise a signal for nations far away,
\q2 and \x + \xo 5:26 \xt ch. 7:18; Zech. 10:8 \x*whistle for them \x + \xo 5:26 \xt ch. 10:3; Deut. 28:49\x*from the ends of the earth;
\q1 and behold, quickly, speedily they come!
\q1
\v 27 \x + \xo 5:27 \xt See ch. 10:28-31\x*None is weary, none stumbles,
\q2 none slumbers or sleeps,
\q1 not a waistband is loose,
\q2 not a sandal strap broken;
\q1
\v 28 \x + \xo 5:28 \xt Ps. 7:12, 13 \x*their arrows are sharp,
\q2 all their bows bent,
\q1 their horses’ hoofs seem like flint,
\q2 and their wheels \x + \xo 5:28 \xt ch. 21:1\x*like the whirlwind.
\q1
\v 29 Their roaring is like a lion,
\q2 like young lions they roar;
\q1 they growl and \x + \xo 5:29 \xt See 2 Kgs. 18:13-16\x*seize their prey;
\q2 they carry it off, and none can rescue.
\q1
\v 30 They will growl over it on that day,
\q2 like the growling of the sea.
\q1 And if one looks to the land,
\q2 behold, \x + \xo 5:30 \xt ch. 8:22\x*darkness and distress;
\q1 and the light is darkened by its clouds.
\c 6
\s1 Isaiah’s Vision of the Lord
\p
\v 1 In the year that \x + \xo 6:1 \xt ch. 1:1; 2 Chr. 26:16-21 \x*King Uzziah died I \x + \xo 6:1 \xt [John 12:41]\x*saw the Lord sitting upon a throne, high and lifted up; and the train\f + \fr 6:1 \ft Or \fq hem\f* of his robe filled the temple.
\v 2 Above him stood the seraphim. Each had \x + \xo 6:2 \xt Rev. 4:8\x*six wings: with two he covered his face, and with two he covered his feet, and with two he flew.
\v 3 And one called to another and said:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 6:3 \xt [See ver. 2 above] \x*“Holy, holy, holy is the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts;
\q1 \x + \xo 6:3 \xt Ps. 72:19\x*the whole earth is full of his glory!”\f + \fr 6:3 \ft Or \fq may his glory fill the whole earth\f*
\b
\m
\v 4 And \x + \xo 6:4 \xt Amos 9:1 \x*the foundations of the thresholds shook at the voice of him who called, and \x + \xo 6:4 \xt 1 Kgs. 8:10, 11; Rev. 15:8; [Ex. 19:18]\x*the house was filled with smoke.
\v 5 And I said: “Woe is me! \x + \xo 6:5 \xt [Judg. 13:22] \x*For I am lost; \x + \xo 6:5 \xt [Luke 5:8] \x*for I am a man of unclean lips, and I dwell in the midst of a people of unclean lips; for my eyes have seen the \x + \xo 6:5 \xt ch. 33:17; Jer. 10:10; [1 Sam. 12:12]\x*King, the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts!”
\p
\v 6 Then one of the seraphim flew to me, having in his hand a burning coal that he had taken with tongs from the altar.
\v 7 And he \x + \xo 6:7 \xt Jer. 1:9; Dan. 10:16\x*touched my mouth and said: “Behold, this has touched your lips; your guilt is taken away, and your sin atoned for.”
\s1 Isaiah’s Commission from the Lord
\p
\v 8 And I heard the voice of the Lord saying, “Whom shall I send, and who will go for \x + \xo 6:8 \xt See Gen. 1:26\x*us?” Then I said, “Here I am! Send me.”
\v 9 And he said, “Go, and say to this people:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 6:9 \xt Cited Matt. 13:14, 15; Acts 28:26, 27; [Mark 4:12; Luke 8:10; Rom. 11:8]\x*“‘Keep on hearing,\f + \fr 6:9 \ft Or \fq Hear indeed\f* but do not understand;
\q1 keep on seeing,\f + \fr 6:9 \ft Or \fq see indeed\f* but do not perceive.’
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 6:10 \xt Cited John 12:40 \x*Make the heart of this people \x + \xo 6:10 \xt Ps. 119:70 \x*dull,\f + \fr 6:10 \ft Hebrew \fq fat\f*
\q2 and their ears heavy,
\q2 and blind their eyes;
\q1 \x + \xo 6:10 \xt [Jer. 5:21]\x*lest they see with their eyes,
\q2 and hear with their ears,
\q1 and understand with their hearts,
\q2 and turn and be healed.”
\q1
\v 11 Then I said, \x + \xo 6:11 \xt Ps. 79:5; 89:46 \x*“How long, O Lord?”
\q1 And he said:
\q1 “Until \x + \xo 6:11 \xt [ch. 1:7; 27:10]\x*cities lie waste
\q2 without inhabitant,
\q1 and houses without people,
\q2 and the land is a desolate waste,
\q1
\v 12 and the \nd Lord\nd* removes people far away,
\q2 and the forsaken places are many in the midst of the land.
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 6:13 \xt [ch. 10:22] \x*And though a tenth remain in it,
\q2 it will be burned\f + \fr 6:13 \ft Or \fq purged\f* again,
\q1 like a terebinth or an oak,
\q2 whose stump \x + \xo 6:13 \xt [Job 14:7] \x*remains
\q2 when it is felled.”
\q1 \x + \xo 6:13 \xt Ezra 9:2\x*The holy seed\f + \fr 6:13 \ft Or \fq offspring\f* is its stump.
\c 7
\s1 Isaiah Sent to King Ahaz
\p
\v 1 In the days of \x + \xo 7:1 \xt ch. 1:1 \x*Ahaz the son of Jotham, son of Uzziah, king of Judah, \x + \xo 7:1 \xt 2 Kgs. 15:37; 16:5\x*Rezin the king of Syria and \x + \xo 7:1 \xt 2 Kgs. 15:37; 16:5\x*Pekah the son of Remaliah the king of Israel came up to Jerusalem to wage war against it, but could not yet mount an attack against it.
\v 2 When the house of David was told, \x + \xo 7:2 \xt [ch. 8:12] \x*“Syria is in league with\f + \fr 7:2 \ft Hebrew \fq Syria has rested upon\f* \x + \xo 7:2 \xt ch. 9:9\x*Ephraim,” the heart of Ahaz\f + \fr 7:2 \ft Hebrew \fq his heart\f* and the heart of his people shook as the trees of the forest shake before the wind.
\p
\v 3 And the \nd Lord\nd* said to Isaiah, “Go out to meet Ahaz, you and \x + \xo 7:3 \xt [ch. 8:3, 18] \x*Shear-jashub\f + \fr 7:3 \fq Shear-jashub \ft means \fq A remnant shall return\f* your son, at the end of \x + \xo 7:3 \xt ch. 36:2; 2 Kgs. 18:17\x*the conduit of the upper pool on the highway to the Washer’s Field.
\v 4 And say to him, \x + \xo 7:4 \xt [ch. 8:12] \x*‘Be careful, \x + \xo 7:4 \xt [Ex. 14:13] \x*be quiet, do not fear, and do not let your heart be faint because of these two \x + \xo 7:4 \xt [Amos 4:11; Zech. 3:2] \x*smoldering stumps of firebrands, at the fierce anger of Rezin and Syria and \x + \xo 7:4 \xt ver. 1\x*the son of Remaliah.
\v 5 Because Syria, with Ephraim and \x + \xo 7:5 \xt [See ver. 4 above]\x*the son of Remaliah, has devised evil against you, saying,
\v 6 “Let us go up against Judah and terrify it, and let us conquer it\f + \fr 7:6 \ft Hebrew \fq let us split it open\f* for ourselves, and set up the son of Tabeel as king in the midst of it,”
\v 7 thus says the Lord \nd God\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 7:7 \xt ch. 8:10\x*“‘It shall not stand,
\q2 and it shall not come to pass.
\q1
\v 8 For the head of Syria is \x + \xo 7:8 \xt Gen. 14:15\x*Damascus,
\q2 and the head of Damascus is Rezin.
\q1 And within sixty-five years
\q2 Ephraim will be shattered from being a people.
\q1
\v 9 And the head of Ephraim is Samaria,
\q2 and the head of Samaria is \x + \xo 7:9 \xt ver. 1 \x*the son of Remaliah.
\q1 \x + \xo 7:9 \xt [2 Chr. 20:20]\x*If you\f + \fr 7:9 \ft The Hebrew for \fq you \ft is plural in verses 9, 13, 14\f* are not firm in faith,
\q2 you will not be firm at all.’”
\s1 The Sign of Immanuel
\p
\v 10 Again the \nd Lord\nd* spoke to Ahaz,
\v 11 “Ask \x + \xo 7:11 \xt See 2 Kgs. 19:29\x*a sign of the \nd Lord\nd* your\f + \fr 7:11 \ft The Hebrew for \fq you \ft and \fq your \ft is singular in verses 11, 16, 17\f* God; let it be deep as Sheol or high as heaven.”
\v 12 But Ahaz said, “I will not ask, and I will not put the \nd Lord\nd* to the test.”
\v 13 And he\f + \fr 7:13 \ft That is, Isaiah\f* said, “Hear then, O house of David! Is it too little for you to weary men, that you \x + \xo 7:13 \xt ch. 43:24\x*weary my God also?
\v 14 Therefore the \x + \xo 7:14 \xt ch. 37:30; 38:7, 8 \x*Lord himself will give you a sign. \x + \xo 7:14 \xt ch. 9:6; Cited Matt. 1:23; [Luke 1:31, 34] \x*Behold, the \x + \xo 7:14 \xt Gen. 24:43 (Heb.); Ex. 2:8 (Heb.); Ps. 68:25 (Heb.); Prov. 30:19 (Heb.) \x*virgin shall conceive and bear a son, and shall call his name \x + \xo 7:14 \xt ch. 8:8, 10\x*Immanuel.\f + \fr 7:14 \fq Immanuel \ft means \fq God is with us\f*
\v 15 He shall eat \x + \xo 7:15 \xt ver. 22\x*curds and honey when he knows how to refuse the evil and choose the good.
\v 16 \x + \xo 7:16 \xt [ch. 8:4] \x*For before the boy knows how to refuse the evil and choose the good, the land whose two kings you dread will be \x + \xo 7:16 \xt ch. 6:12\x*deserted.
\v 17 \x + \xo 7:17 \xt ch. 8:7; [2 Chr. 28:20] \x*The \nd Lord\nd* will bring upon you and upon your people and upon your father’s house such days as have not come since the day that \x + \xo 7:17 \xt 1 Kgs. 12:16\x*Ephraim departed from Judah—the king of Assyria.”
\p
\v 18 In that day the \nd Lord\nd* will \x + \xo 7:18 \xt ch. 5:26\x*whistle for the fly that is at the end of the streams of Egypt, and for the bee that is in the land of Assyria.
\v 19 And they will all come and settle in the steep ravines, and \x + \xo 7:19 \xt ch. 2:19; Jer. 13:4; 16:16\x*in the clefts of the rocks, and on all the thornbushes, and on all the pastures.\f + \fr 7:19 \ft Or \fq watering holes\ft , or \fq brambles\f*
\p
\v 20 In that day \x + \xo 7:20 \xt ch. 24:1; See 2 Kgs. 18:13-16 \x*the Lord will \x + \xo 7:20 \xt Ezek. 5:1 \x*shave with a razor that is \x + \xo 7:20 \xt [ch. 10:5, 15] \x*hired beyond \x + \xo 7:20 \xt ch. 8:7; 11:15\x*the River—with the king of Assyria—the head and the hair of the feet, and it will sweep away the beard also.
\p
\v 21 \x + \xo 7:21 \xt [ch. 5:17]\x*In that day a man will keep alive a young cow and two sheep,
\v 22 and because of the abundance of milk that they give, he will eat curds, for everyone who is left in the land will eat \x + \xo 7:22 \xt ver. 15\x*curds and honey.
\p
\v 23 In that day every place where there used to be a thousand vines, worth a thousand shekels\f + \fr 7:23 \ft A \fq shekel \ft was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams\f* of silver, will become \x + \xo 7:23 \xt ch. 5:6\x*briers and thorns.
\v 24 \x + \xo 7:24 \xt [Judg. 5:11]\x*With bow and arrows a man will come there, for all the land will be briers and thorns.
\v 25 \x + \xo 7:25 \xt ch. 32:13, 14 \x*And as for all the hills that used to be hoed with a hoe, you will not come there for fear \x + \xo 7:25 \xt [See ver. 23 above]\x*of briers and thorns, but they will become a place where cattle are let loose and where sheep tread.
\c 8
\s1 The Coming Assyrian Invasion
\p
\v 1 Then the \nd Lord\nd* said to me, “Take a large tablet \x + \xo 8:1 \xt ch. 30:8\x*and write on it in common characters,\f + \fr 8:1 \ft Hebrew \fq with a man’s stylus\f* ‘Belonging to Maher-shalal-hash-baz.’\f + \fr 8:1 \fq Maher-shalal-hash-baz \ft means \fq The spoil speeds, the prey hastens\f*
\v 2 And \x + \xo 8:2 \xt [ch. 43:10] \x*I will get reliable witnesses, \x + \xo 8:2 \xt 2 Kgs. 16:10, 11, 15, 16\x*Uriah the priest and Zechariah the son of Jeberechiah, to attest for me.”
\p
\v 3 And I went to the prophetess, and she conceived and bore a son. Then the \nd Lord\nd* said to me, \x + \xo 8:3 \xt [Hos. 1:4]\x*“Call his name Maher-shalal-hash-baz;
\v 4 \x + \xo 8:4 \xt [ch. 7:16] \x*for before the boy knows how to cry ‘My father’ or ‘My mother,’ the \x + \xo 8:4 \xt [ch. 7:16] \x*wealth of \x + \xo 8:4 \xt See ch. 7:8, 9\x*Damascus and the spoil of \x + \xo 8:4 \xt See ch. 7:8, 9\x*Samaria will be carried away before the king of Assyria.”
\p
\v 5 The \nd Lord\nd* spoke to me again:
\v 6 “Because this people has refused the waters of \x + \xo 8:6 \xt [Neh. 3:15; John 9:7, 11] \x*Shiloah that flow gently, and rejoice over \x + \xo 8:6 \xt See ch. 7:1, 4\x*Rezin and the son of Remaliah,
