\v 9 \x + \xo 11:9 \xt [See ver. 6 above] \x*They shall not hurt or destroy
\q2 in all \x + \xo 11:9 \xt Ps. 78:54 \x*my holy mountain;
\q1 \x + \xo 11:9 \xt Hab. 2:14\x*for the earth shall be full of the knowledge of the \nd Lord\nd*
\q2 as the waters cover the sea.
\b
\p
\v 10 In that day \x + \xo 11:10 \xt Cited Rom. 15:12 \x*the root of \x + \xo 11:10 \xt ver. 1 \x*Jesse, who shall stand as \x + \xo 11:10 \xt ch. 49:22; [Ex. 17:15]\x*a signal for the peoples—of him shall the nations inquire, and his resting place shall be glorious.
\p
\v 11 \x + \xo 11:11 \xt ch. 10:20 \x*In that day the Lord will extend his hand yet a second time to recover the remnant that remains of his people, \x + \xo 11:11 \xt ch. 27:13; Mic. 7:12; Zech. 10:10 \x*from Assyria, \x + \xo 11:11 \xt ch. 27:13; Mic. 7:12; Zech. 10:10 \x*from Egypt, from \x + \xo 11:11 \xt Jer. 44:1, 15; Ezek. 29:14; 30:14 \x*Pathros, from \x + \xo 11:11 \xt See Gen. 10:6-12 \x*Cush,\f + \fr 11:11 \ft Probably \fq Nubia\f* from \x + \xo 11:11 \xt Gen. 10:22; 14:1, 9; Jer. 25:25; See Jer. 49:34-39 \x*Elam, from \x + \xo 11:11 \xt Gen. 11:2 \x*Shinar, from \x + \xo 11:11 \xt See ch. 10:9 \x*Hamath, and from \x + \xo 11:11 \xt Esth. 10:1\x*the coastlands of the sea.
\b
\q1
\v 12 He will raise \x + \xo 11:12 \xt [See ver. 10 above] \x*a signal for the nations
\q2 and will assemble \x + \xo 11:12 \xt ch. 56:8; [Zech. 10:6]\x*the banished of Israel,
\q1 and gather the dispersed of Judah
\q2 from the four corners of the earth.
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 11:13 \xt Ezek. 37:16, 17; [ch. 9:21; Zech. 11:14]\x*The jealousy of Ephraim shall depart,
\q2 and those who harass Judah shall be cut off;
\q1 Ephraim shall not be jealous of Judah,
\q2 and Judah shall not harass Ephraim.
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 11:14 \xt [2 Sam. 8:1; 2 Kgs. 18:8] \x*But they shall swoop down on the shoulder of the Philistines in the west,
\q2 and together they shall plunder \x + \xo 11:14 \xt Judg. 6:3; See Jer. 49:28 \x*the people of the east.
\q1 They shall put out their hand \x + \xo 11:14 \xt Ps. 60:8 \x*against \x + \xo 11:14 \xt [2 Sam. 8:14] \x*Edom and \x + \xo 11:14 \xt [2 Sam. 8:2] \x*Moab,
\q2 and \x + \xo 11:14 \xt See 2 Sam. 12:26-31\x*the Ammonites shall obey them.
\q1
\v 15 And the \nd Lord\nd* will utterly destroy\f + \fr 11:15 \ft Hebrew \fq devote to destruction\f*
\q2 \x + \xo 11:15 \xt [Zech. 10:11] \x*the tongue of the Sea of Egypt,
\q1 and will wave his hand over \x + \xo 11:15 \xt See ch. 7:20\x*the River
\q2 with his scorching breath,\f + \fr 11:15 \ft Or \fq wind\f*
\q1 and strike it into seven channels,
\q2 and he will lead people across in sandals.
\q1
\v 16 And there will be \x + \xo 11:16 \xt ch. 19:23; [ch. 35:8] \x*a highway from Assyria
\q2 for the remnant that remains of his people,
\q1 \x + \xo 11:16 \xt Ex. 14:29\x*as there was for Israel
\q2 when they came up from the land of Egypt.
\c 12
\s1 The \nd Lord\nd* Is My Strength and My Song
\q1
\v 1 You\f + \fr 12:1 \ft The Hebrew for \fq you \ft is singular in verse 1\f* will say \x + \xo 12:1 \xt ch. 11:11 \x*in that day:
\q1 “I will give thanks to you, O \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 for though you were angry with me,
\q1 \x + \xo 12:1 \xt [ch. 10:4]\x*your anger turned away,
\q2 that you might comfort me.
\b
\q1
\v 2 “Behold, God is my salvation;
\q2 I will trust, and will not be afraid;
\q1 for \x + \xo 12:2 \xt Ex. 15:2; Ps. 118:14\x*the \nd Lord\nd* \nd God\nd*\f + \fr 12:2 \ft Hebrew \fq for Yah, the \+bdit Lord\+bdit* \f* is my strength and my song,
\q2 and he has become my salvation.”
\b
\p
\v 3 \x + \xo 12:3 \xt [John 4:13, 14; 7:37, 38]\x*With joy you\f + \fr 12:3 \ft The Hebrew for \fq you \ft is plural in verses 3, 4\f* will draw water from the wells of salvation.
\v 4 \x + \xo 12:4 \xt ch. 11:11 \x*And you will say in that day:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 12:4 \xt Ps. 105:1 \x*“Give thanks to the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 call upon his name,
\q1 \x + \xo 12:4 \xt [Ps. 145:4-6] \x*make known his deeds among the peoples,
\q2 proclaim \x + \xo 12:4 \xt Ps. 148:13\x*that his name is exalted.
\b
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 12:5 \xt Ex. 15:1; Ps. 98:1\x*“Sing praises to the \nd Lord\nd*, for he has done gloriously;
\q2 let this be made known\f + \fr 12:5 \ft Or \fq this is made known\f* in all the earth.
\q1
\v 6 Shout, and sing for joy, O inhabitant of Zion,
\q2 for great \x + \xo 12:6 \xt Ps. 46:5; Hos. 11:9 \x*in your\f + \fr 12:6 \ft The Hebrew for \fq your \ft in verse 6 is singular, referring to the \fq inhabitant of Zion\f* midst is \x + \xo 12:6 \xt ch. 5:24; 41:14, 16\x*the Holy One of Israel.”
\c 13
\s1 The Judgment of Babylon
\p
\v 1 The oracle concerning \x + \xo 13:1 \xt ver. 19; ch. 14:4; 21:9; 47:1; See Jer. 51, 52 \x*Babylon which \x + \xo 13:1 \xt ch. 1:1\x*Isaiah the son of Amoz saw.
\b
\q1
\v 2 On a bare hill \x + \xo 13:2 \xt ch. 5:26 \x*raise a signal;
\q2 cry aloud to them;
\q1 wave the hand for \x + \xo 13:2 \xt [ch. 41:25]\x*them to enter
\q2 the gates of the nobles.
\q1
\v 3 I myself have commanded my consecrated ones,
\q2 and have summoned my mighty men to execute my anger,
\q2 my proudly exulting ones.\f + \fr 13:3 \ft Or \fq those who exult in my majesty\f*
\b
\q1
\v 4 The sound \x + \xo 13:4 \xt [ch. 22:5] \x*of a tumult is on the mountains
\q2 as of a great multitude!
\q1 The sound of an uproar of kingdoms,
\q2 of nations gathering together!
\q1 \x + \xo 13:4 \xt [Josh. 5:13, 14]\x*The \nd Lord\nd* of hosts is mustering
\q2 a host for battle.
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 13:5 \xt [ch. 46:11]\x*They come from a distant land,
\q2 from the end of the heavens,
\q1 the \nd Lord\nd* and the weapons of his indignation,
\q2 to destroy the whole land.\f + \fr 13:5 \ft Or \fq earth\ft ; also verse 9\f*
\b
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 13:6 \xt ch. 14:31; 15:2, 3, 8; 16:7; Jer. 51:8; Ezek. 30:2 \x*Wail, for \x + \xo 13:6 \xt ch. 2:12; Joel 1:15; Zeph. 1:7\x*the day of the \nd Lord\nd* is near;
\q2 as destruction from the Almighty\f + \fr 13:6 \ft The Hebrew words for \fq destruction \ft and \fq almighty \ft sound alike\f* it will come!
\q1
\v 7 Therefore all hands will be feeble,
\q2 and every human heart \x + \xo 13:7 \xt See Josh. 2:11\x*will melt.
\q1
\v 8 They will be dismayed:
\q2 \x + \xo 13:8 \xt [Nah. 2:10] \x*pangs and agony will seize them;
\q2 \x + \xo 13:8 \xt ch. 26:17; Jer. 4:31; 6:24; Mic. 4:9, 10; John 16:21\x*they will be in anguish like a woman in labor.
\q1 They will look aghast at one another;
\q2 their faces will be aflame.
\b
\q1
\v 9 Behold, \x + \xo 13:9 \xt [See ver. 6 above] \x*the day of the \nd Lord\nd* comes,
\q2 cruel, with wrath and fierce anger,
\q1 to make the land a desolation
\q2 and \x + \xo 13:9 \xt [Ps. 104:35]\x*to destroy its sinners from it.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 13:10 \xt [ch. 34:4] \x*For the stars of the heavens and their constellations
\q2 will not give their light;
\q1 \x + \xo 13:10 \xt Ezek. 32:7; Joel 2:31; 3:15; Matt. 24:29; Mark 13:24; Luke 21:25\x*the sun will be dark at its rising,
\q2 and the moon will not shed its light.
\q1
\v 11 I will punish \x + \xo 13:11 \xt ch. 24:21 \x*the world for its evil,
\q2 and the wicked for their iniquity;
\q1 I will \x + \xo 13:11 \xt [ch. 24:4] \x*put an end to the pomp of the arrogant,
\q2 \x + \xo 13:11 \xt [ch. 2:11, 17]\x*and lay low the pompous pride of the ruthless.
\q1
\v 12 I will make \x + \xo 13:12 \xt ch. 24:6 \x*people more rare than fine gold,
\q2 and mankind than the \x + \xo 13:12 \xt 1 Kgs. 10:11; Job 28:16\x*gold of Ophir.
\q1
\v 13 Therefore \x + \xo 13:13 \xt Hag. 2:6\x*I will make the heavens tremble,
\q2 and the earth will be shaken out of its place,
\q1 at the wrath of the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts
\q2 in the day of his fierce anger.
\q1
\v 14 And like a hunted gazelle,
\q2 or like sheep with none to gather them,
\q1 \x + \xo 13:14 \xt Jer. 50:16; 51:9; [1 Kgs. 22:36]\x*each will turn to his own people,
\q2 and each will flee to his own land.
\q1
\v 15 Whoever is found will be thrust through,
\q2 and whoever is caught will fall by the sword.
\q1
\v 16 \x + \xo 13:16 \xt Ps. 137:9; Nah. 3:10\x*Their infants will be dashed in pieces
\q2 before their eyes;
\q1 their houses will be plundered
\q2 and their wives ravished.
\b
\q1
\v 17 Behold, \x + \xo 13:17 \xt ch. 21:2; Jer. 51:11, 28; Dan. 5:28, 31\x*I am stirring up the Medes against them,
\q2 who have no regard for silver
\q2 and do not delight in gold.
\q1
\v 18 \x + \xo 13:18 \xt Jer. 50:14, 29; 51:3\x*Their bows will slaughter\f + \fr 13:18 \ft Hebrew \fq dash in pieces\f* the young men;
\q2 they will have no mercy on the fruit of the womb;
\q2 their eyes will not pity children.
\q1
\v 19 And Babylon, \x + \xo 13:19 \xt [ch. 47:5] \x*the glory of kingdoms,
\q2 the splendor and pomp of the Chaldeans,
\q1 will be \x + \xo 13:19 \xt ch. 1:9; Gen. 19:24; Jer. 50:40; Amos 4:11\x*like Sodom and Gomorrah
\q2 when God overthrew them.
\q1
\v 20 \x + \xo 13:20 \xt Jer. 51:37, 43 \x*It will never be inhabited
\q2 or lived in for all generations;
\q1 no \x + \xo 13:20 \xt Jer. 3:2 \x*Arab will pitch his tent there;
\q2 no \x + \xo 13:20 \xt Jer. 33:12\x*shepherds will make their flocks lie down there.
\q1
\v 21 But \x + \xo 13:21 \xt [ch. 34:13, 14] \x*wild animals will lie down there,
\q2 and their houses will be full of howling creatures;
\q1 there \x + \xo 13:21 \xt ch. 34:13; Jer. 50:39\x*ostriches\f + \fr 13:21 \ft Or \fq owls\f* will dwell,
\q2 and there wild goats will dance.
\q1
\v 22 Hyenas\f + \fr 13:22 \ft Or \fq foxes\f* will cry in its towers,
\q2 and \x + \xo 13:22 \xt ch. 35:7; Jer. 51:37 \x*jackals in \x + \xo 13:22 \xt [ch. 25:2; Amos 3:15]\x*the pleasant palaces;
\q1 its time is close at hand
\q2 and its days will not be prolonged.
\c 14
\s1 The Restoration of Jacob
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 14:1 \xt Ps. 102:13; Zech. 1:17 \x*For the \nd Lord\nd* will have compassion on Jacob and will again choose Israel, and \x + \xo 14:1 \xt 2 Chr. 36:22, 23 \x*will set them in their own land, and \x + \xo 14:1 \xt Zech. 8:22, 23; See Eph. 2:12-14\x*sojourners will join them and will attach themselves to the house of Jacob.
\v 2 And \x + \xo 14:2 \xt ch. 49:22; 60:9; 66:20 \x*the peoples will take them and bring them to their place, and the house of Israel will possess them in the \nd Lord\nd*’s land \x + \xo 14:2 \xt ch. 61:5 \x*as male and female slaves.\f + \fr 14:2 \ft Or \fq servants\f* \x + \xo 14:2 \xt [Joel 3:8] \x*They will take captive those who were their captors, \x + \xo 14:2 \xt ch. 60:14\x*and rule over those who oppressed them.
\s1 Israel’s Remnant Taunts Babylon
\p
\v 3 When the \nd Lord\nd* has given you rest from your pain and turmoil and the hard service with which you were made to serve,
\v 4 you will take up this \x + \xo 14:4 \xt Mic. 2:4; Hab. 2:6 \x*taunt against the king of Babylon:
\b
\q1 “How the oppressor has ceased,
\q2 \x + \xo 14:4 \xt [Jer. 51:13; Rev. 18:16]\x*the insolent fury\f + \fr 14:4 \ft Dead Sea Scroll (compare Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate); the meaning of the word in the Masoretic Text is uncertain\f* ceased!
\q1
\v 5 The \nd Lord\nd* has broken the \x + \xo 14:5 \xt [ch. 9:4]\x*staff of the wicked,
\q2 the \x + \xo 14:5 \xt [ch. 9:4]\x*scepter of rulers,
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 14:6 \xt [Jer. 50:23]\x*that struck the peoples in wrath
\q2 with unceasing blows,
\q1 that ruled the nations in anger
\q2 with unrelenting persecution.
\q1
\v 7 The whole earth is at rest and quiet;
\q2 \x + \xo 14:7 \xt ch. 44:23; 49:13; 54:1; 55:12\x*they break forth into singing.
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 14:8 \xt [Ezek. 31:16] \x*\x + \xo 14:8 \xt [ch. 37:24] \x*The cypresses rejoice at you,
\q2 \x + \xo 14:8 \xt See ch. 2:13\x*the cedars of Lebanon, saying,
\q1 ‘Since you were laid low,
\q2 no woodcutter comes up against us.’
\q1
\v 9 Sheol beneath is stirred up
\q2 to meet you when you come;
\q1 it rouses the shades to greet you,
\q2 all who were leaders of the earth;
\q1 it raises from their thrones
\q2 all who were kings of the nations.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 14:10 \xt [Jer. 51:48]\x*All of them will answer
\q2 and say to you:
\q1 ‘You too have become as weak as we!
\q2 You have become like us!’
\q1
\v 11 Your pomp is brought down to Sheol,
\q2 the sound of your harps;
\q1 maggots are laid as a bed beneath you,
\q2 and worms are your covers.
\b
\q1
\v 12 “How \x + \xo 14:12 \xt [ch. 24:21; 34:3] \x*you are fallen from heaven,
\q2 O Day Star, \x + \xo 14:12 \xt [Job 38:7]\x*son of Dawn!
\q1 How you are cut down to the ground,
\q2 you who laid the nations low!
\q1
\v 13 You said in your heart,
\q2 \x + \xo 14:13 \xt Jer. 51:53; Amos 9:2; [Matt. 11:23; Luke 10:15] \x*‘I will ascend to heaven;
\q1 above the stars of God
\q2 \x + \xo 14:13 \xt Dan. 5:22, 23; [2 Thess. 2:4]\x*I will set my throne on high;
\q1 I will sit on the mount of assembly
\q2 in the far reaches of the north;\f + \fr 14:13 \ft Or \fq in the remote parts of Zaphon\f*
\q1
\v 14 I will ascend above the heights of the clouds;
\q2 I will make myself like the Most High.’
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 14:15 \xt Ezek. 32:23; Matt. 11:23; Luke 10:15\x*But you are brought down to Sheol,
\q2 to the far reaches of the pit.
\q1
\v 16 Those who see you will stare at you
\q2 and ponder over you:
\q1 ‘Is this \x + \xo 14:16 \xt [Jer. 50:23]\x*the man who made the earth tremble,
\q2 who shook kingdoms,
\q1
\v 17 who made the world like a desert
\q2 and overthrew its cities,
\q2 \x + \xo 14:17 \xt [Jer. 50:33]\x*who did not let his prisoners go home?’
\q1
\v 18 All the kings of the nations lie in glory,
\q2 each in his own tomb;\f + \fr 14:18 \ft Hebrew \fq house\f*
\q1
\v 19 but you are cast out, away from your grave,
\q2 like a loathed branch,
\q1 \x + \xo 14:19 \xt [Ezek. 32:20]\x*clothed with the slain, those pierced by the sword,
\q2 who go down to the stones of the pit,
\q2 like a dead body trampled underfoot.
\q1
\v 20 You will not be joined with them in burial,
\q2 because you have destroyed your land,
\q2 you have slain your people.
\b
\q1 “May \x + \xo 14:20 \xt Job 18:19; Ps. 21:10; 109:13\x*the offspring of evildoers
\q2 nevermore be named!
\q1
\v 21 Prepare slaughter for his sons
\q2 \x + \xo 14:21 \xt [Ex. 20:5; Matt. 23:35]\x*because of the guilt of their fathers,
\q1 lest they rise and possess the earth,
\q2 and fill the face of the world with cities.”
\b
\p
\v 22 “I will rise up against them,” declares the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, “and will cut off from Babylon name and \x + \xo 14:22 \xt [Jer. 51:50, 62] \x*remnant, \x + \xo 14:22 \xt Job 18:19; [Gen. 21:23]\x*descendants and posterity,” declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\v 23 “And I will make it a possession of the \x + \xo 14:23 \xt ch. 34:11; Zeph. 2:14\x*hedgehog,\f + \fr 14:23 \ft Possibly \fq porcupine\ft , or \fq owl\f* and pools of water, and I will sweep it with the broom of destruction,” declares the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts.
\s1 An Oracle Concerning Assyria
\q1
\v 24 The \nd Lord\nd* of hosts has sworn:
\q1 \x + \xo 14:24 \xt [Prov. 19:21]\x*“As I have planned,
\q2 so shall it be,
\q1 and as I have purposed,
\q2 so shall it stand,
\q1
\v 25 that \x + \xo 14:25 \xt ch. 37:36 \x*I will break the Assyrian in my land,
\q2 and on my mountains trample him underfoot;
\q1 and \x + \xo 14:25 \xt ch. 9:4; 10:27\x*his yoke shall depart from them,
\q2 and \x + \xo 14:25 \xt ch. 9:4; 10:27\x*his burden from their shoulder.”
\b
\q1
\v 26 This is the purpose that is purposed
\q2 concerning the whole earth,
\q1 and this is \x + \xo 14:26 \xt [Deut. 4:34]\x*the hand that is stretched out
\q2 over all the nations.
\q1
\v 27 \x + \xo 14:27 \xt 2 Chr. 20:6; Job 9:12; Ps. 33:11; Prov. 21:30; Dan. 4:31, 33, 35 \x*For the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts has purposed,
\q2 and who will annul it?
\q1 \x + \xo 14:27 \xt [See ver. 26 above]\x*His hand is stretched out,
\q2 and who will turn it back?
\s1 An Oracle Concerning Philistia
\p
\v 28 In the year that \x + \xo 14:28 \xt 2 Kgs. 16:20 \x*King Ahaz died came this \x + \xo 14:28 \xt See ch. 13:1\x*oracle:
\b
\q1
\v 29 Rejoice not, \x + \xo 14:29 \xt Ex. 15:14; [Ps. 60:8; 87:4; 108:9] \x*O Philistia, all of you,
\q2 that \x + \xo 14:29 \xt [ch. 10:24] \x*the rod that struck you is broken,
\q1 for from the serpent’s root will come forth an adder,
\q2 and its fruit will be a \x + \xo 14:29 \xt ch. 30:6; Num. 21:6; [Jer. 46:22]\x*flying fiery serpent.
\q1
\v 30 And the firstborn of \x + \xo 14:30 \xt [ch. 29:19; Zeph. 3:12]\x*the poor will graze,
\q2 and \x + \xo 14:30 \xt [ch. 29:19; Zeph. 3:12]\x*the needy lie down in safety;
\q1 but I will kill your root with famine,
\q2 and your remnant it will slay.
\q1
\v 31 \x + \xo 14:31 \xt ch. 13:6 \x*Wail, O \x + \xo 14:31 \xt ch. 24:12 \x*gate; cry out, O city;
\q2 melt in fear, \x + \xo 14:31 \xt [See ver. 29 above] \x*O Philistia, all of you!
\q1 \x + \xo 14:31 \xt [ch. 20:1]\x*For smoke comes out of the north,
\q2 and there is no straggler in his ranks.
\b
\q1
\v 32 What will one answer the messengers of the nation?
\q1 \x + \xo 14:32 \xt Ps. 87:1, 5; 102:16; 132:13; [ch. 28:16]\x*“The \nd Lord\nd* has founded Zion,
\q2 and in her the afflicted of his people find refuge.”
\c 15
\s1 An Oracle Concerning Moab
\p
\v 1 An \x + \xo 15:1 \xt [See ch. 14:28 above] \x*oracle concerning \x + \xo 15:1 \xt See Jer. 48; Ezek. 25:8-11; Amos 2:1-3; Zeph. 2:8, 9 \x*Moab.
\b
\q1 Because \x + \xo 15:1 \xt Num. 21:15, 28 \x*Ar of Moab is laid waste in a night,
\q2 Moab is undone;
\q1 because \x + \xo 15:1 \xt [ch. 16:7, 11]\x*Kir of Moab is laid waste in a night,
\q2 Moab is undone.
\q1
\v 2 He has gone up to the temple,\f + \fr 15:2 \ft Hebrew \fq the house\f* and to \x + \xo 15:2 \xt Num. 21:30 \x*Dibon,
\q2 to the high places\f + \fr 15:2 \ft Or \fq temple, even Dibon to the high places\f* to weep;
\q1 over \x + \xo 15:2 \xt Deut. 34:1 \x*Nebo and over \x + \xo 15:2 \xt Num. 21:30 \x*Medeba
\q2 Moab \x + \xo 15:2 \xt ch. 13:6 \x*wails.
\q1 On every head is \x + \xo 15:2 \xt See ch. 3:24\x*baldness;
\q2 every beard is shorn;
\q1
\v 3 in the streets they wear sackcloth;
\q2 on the housetops and in the squares
\q2 everyone wails and melts in tears.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 15:4 \xt Num. 32:37 \x*Heshbon and \x + \xo 15:4 \xt Num. 32:37 \x*Elealeh cry out;
\q2 their voice is heard as far as \x + \xo 15:4 \xt Jer. 48:34\x*Jahaz;
\q1 therefore the armed men of Moab cry aloud;
\q2 his soul trembles.
\q1
\v 5 My heart cries out for Moab;
\q2 her fugitives flee to Zoar,
\q2 to \x + \xo 15:5 \xt [See ver. 4 above] \x*Eglath-shelishiyah.
\q1 For at the \x + \xo 15:5 \xt Jer. 48:5\x*ascent of Luhith
\q2 they go up weeping;
\q1 on the road to \x + \xo 15:5 \xt Jer. 48:5\x*Horonaim
\q2 they raise a cry of destruction;
\q1
\v 6 the waters of \x + \xo 15:6 \xt [Num. 32:36]\x*Nimrim
\q2 are a desolation;
\q1 the grass is withered, the vegetation fails,
\q2 the greenery is no more.
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 15:7 \xt Jer. 48:36\x*Therefore the abundance they have gained
\q2 and what they have laid up
\q1 they carry away
\q2 over the Brook of the Willows.
\q1
\v 8 For a cry has gone
\q2 around the land of Moab;
\q1 her wailing reaches to Eglaim;
\q2 her wailing reaches to Beer-elim.
\q1
\v 9 For the waters of \x + \xo 15:9 \xt [ver. 2] \x*Dibon\f + \fr 15:9 \ft Dead Sea Scroll, Vulgate (compare Syriac); Masoretic Text \fq Dimon\ft ; twice in this verse\f* are full of blood;
\q2 for I will bring upon Dibon even more,
\q1 \x + \xo 15:9 \xt [2 Kgs. 17:25; Jer. 50:17]\x*a lion for those of Moab who escape,
\q2 for the remnant of the land.
\c 16
\q1
\v 1 \x + \xo 16:1 \xt 2 Kgs. 3:4 \x*Send the lamb to the ruler of the land,
\q1 from \x + \xo 16:1 \xt ch. 42:11; 2 Kgs. 14:7\x*Sela, by way of the desert,
\q2 to the mount of the daughter of Zion.
\q1
\v 2 Like fleeing birds,
\q2 like a scattered nest,
\q1 so are the daughters of Moab
\q2 at \x + \xo 16:2 \xt Judg. 11:18\x*the fords of the Arnon.
\b
\q1
\v 3 “Give counsel;
\q2 grant justice;
\q1 \x + \xo 16:3 \xt [1 Kgs. 18:4]\x*make your shade like night
\q2 at the height of noon;
\q1 shelter the outcasts;
\q2 do not reveal the fugitive;
\q1
\v 4 let \x + \xo 16:4 \xt 1 Sam. 22:3\x*the outcasts of Moab
\q2 sojourn among you;
\q1 be a shelter to them\f + \fr 16:4 \ft Some Hebrew manuscripts, Septuagint, Syriac; Masoretic Text \fq let my outcasts sojourn among you; as for Moab, be a shelter to them\f*
\q2 from the destroyer.
\q1 When the oppressor is no more,
\q2 and destruction has ceased,
\q1 and he who tramples underfoot has vanished from the land,
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 16:5 \xt ch. 32:1, 2; Dan. 7:14, 27; Mic. 4:7; Luke 1:33\x*then a throne will be established in steadfast love,
\q2 and on it will sit in faithfulness
\q2 in the tent of David
\q1 one who judges and seeks justice
\q2 and is swift to do righteousness.”
\b
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 16:6 \xt Jer. 48:29; Zeph. 2:10 \x*We have heard of the pride of Moab—
\q2 how proud he is!—
\q1 \x + \xo 16:6 \xt Judg. 3:14; 2 Kgs. 13:20; [2 Chr. 20:1]\x*of his arrogance, his pride, and his insolence;
\q2 in his idle boasting he is not right.
\q1
\v 7 Therefore let Moab wail for Moab,
\q2 \x + \xo 16:7 \xt ch. 15:3 \x*let everyone wail.
\q1 Mourn, utterly stricken,
\q2 for the \x + \xo 16:7 \xt 2 Sam. 6:19; [ver. 9] \x*raisin cakes of \x + \xo 16:7 \xt 2 Kgs. 3:25; [ch. 15:1]\x*Kir-hareseth.
\b
\q1
\v 8 For the fields of Heshbon languish,
\q2 and \x + \xo 16:8 \xt Jer. 48:32\x*the vine of Sibmah;
\q1 the lords of the nations
\q2 have struck down its branches,
\q1 which reached to Jazer
\q2 and strayed to the desert;
\q1 its shoots spread abroad
\q2 and passed over the sea.
\q1
\v 9 Therefore \x + \xo 16:9 \xt [ch. 15:5] \x*I weep with \x + \xo 16:9 \xt [See ver. 8 above] \x*the weeping of Jazer
\q2 for the vine of Sibmah;
\q1 I drench you with my tears,
\q2 O Heshbon and Elealeh;
\q1 for over \x + \xo 16:9 \xt [ver. 7]\x*your summer fruit and your harvest
\q2 the shout has ceased.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 16:10 \xt Jer. 48:33 \x*And joy and gladness are taken away from \x + \xo 16:10 \xt [ch. 9:3] \x*the fruitful field,
\q1 and in the vineyards no \x + \xo 16:10 \xt [Judg. 9:27] \x*songs are sung,
\q2 no cheers are raised;
\q1 no \x + \xo 16:10 \xt ch. 63:3; Jer. 25:30 \x*treader treads out wine \x + \xo 16:10 \xt ch. 5:2\x*in the presses;
\q2 I have put an end to the shouting.
\q1
\v 11 Therefore \x + \xo 16:11 \xt ch. 15:5; Jer. 48:36\x*my inner parts moan like a lyre for Moab,
\q2 and my inmost self for Kir-hareseth.
\b
\p
\v 12 And when Moab presents himself, when \x + \xo 16:12 \xt [1 Kgs. 18:29] \x*he wearies himself on \x + \xo 16:12 \xt ch. 15:2; [Num. 22:41; 23:14, 28]\x*the high place, when he comes to his sanctuary to pray, he will not prevail.
\p
\v 13 This is the word that the \nd Lord\nd* spoke concerning Moab \x + \xo 16:13 \xt See Amos 2:1-3\x*in the past.
\v 14 But now the \nd Lord\nd* has spoken, saying, “In three years, \x + \xo 16:14 \xt ch. 21:16 \x*like the years of a hired worker, the glory of Moab will be brought into contempt, in spite of all his great multitude, and those who remain will be \x + \xo 16:14 \xt [ch. 10:22]\x*very few and feeble.”
\c 17
\s1 An Oracle Concerning Damascus
\p
\v 1 An \x + \xo 17:1 \xt See ch. 13:1 \x*oracle concerning \x + \xo 17:1 \xt ch. 7:8; Zech. 9:1; See Jer. 49:23-27; Amos 1:3-5\x*Damascus.
\b
\q1 Behold, Damascus will cease to be a city
\q2 and will become a heap of ruins.
\q1
\v 2 The cities of \x + \xo 17:2 \xt Deut. 2:36; Josh. 13:25 \x*Aroer are deserted;
\q2 they will be for flocks,
\q2 which will lie down, and \x + \xo 17:2 \xt Mic. 4:4\x*none will make them afraid.
\q1
\v 3 The fortress will disappear from \x + \xo 17:3 \xt ch. 7:16; 8:4 \x*Ephraim,
\q2 and the kingdom from \x + \xo 17:3 \xt ch. 7:16; 8:4 \x*Damascus;
\q1 and the remnant of Syria will be
\q2 like \x + \xo 17:3 \xt [1 Sam. 4:21]\x*the glory of the children of Israel,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts.
\b
\q1
\v 4 And in that day \x + \xo 17:4 \xt [See ver. 3 above] \x*the glory of Jacob will be brought low,
\q2 and \x + \xo 17:4 \xt ch. 10:16\x*the fat of his flesh will grow lean.
\q1
\v 5 And it shall be \x + \xo 17:5 \xt [ch. 24:1] \x*as when the reaper gathers standing grain
\q2 and his arm harvests the ears,
\q1 and as when one gleans the ears of grain
\q2 in \x + \xo 17:5 \xt See 2 Sam. 5:18\x*the Valley of Rephaim.
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 17:6 \xt ch. 24:13\x*Gleanings will be left in it,
\q2 as when an olive tree is beaten—
\q1 two or three berries
\q2 in the top of the highest bough,
\q1 four or five
\q2 on the branches of a fruit tree,
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd* God of Israel.
\b
\p
\v 7 \x + \xo 17:7 \xt [Hos. 8:14]\x*In that day man will look to his Maker, and his eyes will look on the Holy One of Israel.
\v 8 \x + \xo 17:8 \xt ch. 27:9; Mic. 5:13, 14 \x*He will not look to the altars, the work of his hands, and he will not look on what his own fingers have made, either the \x + \xo 17:8 \xt Ex. 34:13; See Deut. 16:21\x*Asherim or the altars of incense.
\p
\v 9 \x + \xo 17:9 \xt [ch. 27:10]\x*In that day their strong cities will be like the deserted places of the wooded heights and the hilltops, which they deserted because of the children of Israel, and there will be desolation.
\b
\q1
\v 10 For \x + \xo 17:10 \xt Ps. 106:21 \x*you have forgotten the God of your salvation
\q2 and have not remembered the \x + \xo 17:10 \xt ch. 26:4; [Deut. 32:4, 18, 31]\x*Rock of your refuge;
\q1 therefore, though you plant pleasant plants
\q2 and sow the vine-branch of a stranger,
\q1
\v 11 though you make them grow\f + \fr 17:11 \ft Or \fq though you carefully fence them\f* on the day that you plant them,
\q2 and make them blossom in the morning that you sow,
\q1 yet the harvest will flee away\f + \fr 17:11 \ft Or \fq will be a heap\f*
\q2 in a day of grief and incurable pain.
\b
\q1
\v 12 Ah, \x + \xo 17:12 \xt See ch. 22:5-7\x*the thunder of many peoples;
\q2 they thunder like the thundering of the sea!
\q1 Ah, the roar of nations;
\q2 they roar like the roaring of mighty waters!
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 17:13 \xt [ch. 33:3] \x*The nations roar like the roaring of many waters,
\q2 \x + \xo 17:13 \xt Ps. 9:5; [Joel 3:2] \x*but he will rebuke them, and they will flee far away,
\q1 chased \x + \xo 17:13 \xt See Ps. 1:4 \x*like chaff on the mountains before the wind
\q2 and \x + \xo 17:13 \xt Ps. 83:13\x*whirling dust before the storm.
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 17:14 \xt [Ps. 30:5]\x*At evening time, behold, terror!
\q2 Before morning, they are no more!
\q1 This is the portion of those who loot us,
\q2 and the lot of those who plunder us.
\c 18
\s1 An Oracle Concerning Cush
\q1
\v 1 Ah, land of \x + \xo 18:1 \xt [ch. 8:8; 17:12] \x*whirring wings
\q2 that is beyond the rivers of \x + \xo 18:1 \xt 2 Kgs. 19:9\x*Cush,\f + \fr 18:1 \ft Probably \fq Nubia\f*
\q1
\v 2 which \x + \xo 18:2 \xt ch. 30:4 \x*sends ambassadors by the sea,
\q2 in vessels of papyrus on the waters!
\q1 Go, you swift messengers,
\q2 to a nation \x + \xo 18:2 \xt ver. 7 \x*tall and smooth,
\q1 to a people feared near and far,
\q2 a nation \x + \xo 18:2 \xt [2 Sam. 8:2]\x*mighty and conquering,
\q2 whose land the rivers divide.
\b
\q1
\v 3 All you inhabitants of the world,
\q2 you who dwell on the earth,
\q1 when \x + \xo 18:3 \xt See ch. 5:26\x*a signal is raised on the mountains, look!
\q2 When a trumpet is blown, hear!
\q1
\v 4 For thus the \nd Lord\nd* said to me:
\q1 “I will quietly look \x + \xo 18:4 \xt Ps. 11:4\x*from my dwelling
\q2 like clear heat in sunshine,
\q2 like a cloud of dew in the heat of harvest.”
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 18:5 \xt [Ezek. 31:3, 12, 13]\x*For before the harvest, when the blossom is over,
\q2 and the flower becomes a ripening grape,
\q1 he cuts off the shoots with pruning hooks,
\q2 and the spreading branches he lops off and clears away.
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 18:6 \xt [See ver. 5 above]\x*They shall all of them be left
\q2 to the birds of prey of the mountains
\q2 and to the beasts of the earth.
\q1 And the birds of prey will summer on them,
\q2 and all the beasts of the earth will winter on them.
\b
\p
\v 7 \x + \xo 18:7 \xt Ps. 68:31 \x*At that time tribute will be brought to the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts
\b
\q1 from a people \x + \xo 18:7 \xt ver. 2 \x*tall and smooth,
\q2 from a people feared near and far,
\q1 a nation mighty and conquering,
\q2 whose land the rivers divide,
\b
\m to \x + \xo 18:7 \xt [ch. 25:10] \x*Mount Zion, the place of the \x + \xo 18:7 \xt 2 Sam. 7:13\x*name of the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts.
\c 19
\s1 An Oracle Concerning Egypt
\p
\v 1 An \x + \xo 19:1 \xt See ch. 13:1 \x*oracle concerning \x + \xo 19:1 \xt [Joel 3:19]; See Jer. 46:13-26; Ezek. 29:1–31:2; 31:18–32:32 \x*Egypt.
\b
\q1 Behold, the \nd Lord\nd* \x + \xo 19:1 \xt Ps. 18:10, 11; 104:3; [Matt. 26:64; Rev. 1:7] \x*is riding on a swift cloud
\q2 and comes to Egypt;
\q1 and \x + \xo 19:1 \xt Ex. 12:12; [1 Sam. 5:3; Jer. 43:12; 50:2] \x*the idols of Egypt will tremble at his presence,
\q2 and the heart of the Egyptians will \x + \xo 19:1 \xt ch. 13:7; See Josh. 2:11\x*melt within them.
\q1
\v 2 And I will stir up Egyptians against Egyptians,
\q2 \x + \xo 19:2 \xt [Judg. 7:22]\x*and they will fight, each against another
\q2 and each against his neighbor,
\q2 city against city, kingdom against kingdom;
\q1
\v 3 and the spirit of the Egyptians within them will be emptied out,
\q2 and I will confound\f + \fr 19:3 \ft Or \fq I will swallow up\f* their \x + \xo 19:3 \xt ver. 11 \x*counsel;
\q1 and they will inquire of the idols and the sorcerers,
\q2 and \x + \xo 19:3 \xt ch. 8:19\x*the mediums and the necromancers;
\q1
\v 4 and I will give over the Egyptians
\q2 into the hand of \x + \xo 19:4 \xt ch. 20:4; Jer. 46:26; Ezek. 29:19\x*a hard master,
\q1 and a fierce king will rule over them,
\q2 declares the Lord \nd God\nd* of hosts.
\b
\q1
\v 5 And the waters of the sea will be dried up,
\q2 and the river will be dry and parched,
\q1
\v 6 and its canals will become foul,
\q2 and the branches of Egypt’s Nile will diminish and dry up,
\q2 reeds and rushes will rot away.
\q1
\v 7 There will be bare places by the Nile,
\q2 on the brink of the Nile,
\q1 and all that is sown by the Nile will be parched,
\q2 will be driven away, and will be no more.
\q1
\v 8 The \x + \xo 19:8 \xt [Num. 11:5]\x*fishermen will mourn and lament,
\q2 all who cast a hook in the Nile;
\q1 and they will languish
\q2 who spread nets on the water.
\q1
\v 9 The workers in \x + \xo 19:9 \xt [Ezek. 27:7]\x*combed flax will be in despair,
\q2 and the weavers of white cotton.
\q1
\v 10 Those who are the \x + \xo 19:10 \xt [Gal. 2:9] \x*pillars of the land will be crushed,
\q2 and all who \x + \xo 19:10 \xt Jer. 46:21\x*work for pay will be grieved.
\b
\q1
\v 11 The princes of \x + \xo 19:11 \xt ch. 30:4; Num. 13:22; Ps. 78:43\x*Zoan are utterly foolish;
\q2 the wisest counselors of Pharaoh give stupid counsel.
\q1 How can you say to Pharaoh,
\q2 “I am a son of the wise,
\q2 a son of ancient kings”?
\q1
\v 12 Where then are your \x + \xo 19:12 \xt 1 Kgs. 4:30; Acts 7:22\x*wise men?
\q2 Let them tell you
\q2 that they might know what the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts has purposed against Egypt.
\q1
\v 13 The princes of \x + \xo 19:13 \xt [See ver. 11 above] \x*Zoan have become fools,
\q2 and the princes of \x + \xo 19:13 \xt Jer. 2:16; 44:1; 46:14, 19; Ezek. 30:13, 16 \x*Memphis are deluded;
\q1 those who are the \x + \xo 19:13 \xt [Zech. 10:4]\x*cornerstones of her tribes
\q2 have made Egypt stagger.
\q1
\v 14 The \nd Lord\nd* has mingled within her \x + \xo 19:14 \xt [1 Kgs. 22:22] \x*a spirit of confusion,
\q1 and they will make Egypt stagger in all its deeds,
\q2 \x + \xo 19:14 \xt [ch. 24:20; 29:9]\x*as a drunken man staggers in his vomit.
\q1
\v 15 And there will be nothing for Egypt
\q2 that \x + \xo 19:15 \xt ch. 9:14\x*head or tail, palm branch or reed, may do.
\s1 Egypt, Assyria, Israel Blessed
\p
\v 16 In that day the Egyptians will be \x + \xo 19:16 \xt Jer. 50:37; 51:30; Nah. 3:13 \x*like women, and \x + \xo 19:16 \xt ch. 10:32\x*tremble with fear before the hand that the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts shakes over them.
\v 17 And the land of Judah will become a terror to the Egyptians. Everyone to whom it is mentioned will fear because of the purpose that the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts has purposed against them.
\p
\v 18 \x + \xo 19:18 \xt ver. 21 \x*In that day there will be \x + \xo 19:18 \xt [ch. 30:17; 2 Kgs. 7:13] \x*five cities in the land of Egypt that \x + \xo 19:18 \xt [Zeph. 3:9]\x*speak the language of Canaan and swear allegiance to the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts. One of these will be called the City of Destruction.\f + \fr 19:18 \ft Dead Sea Scroll and some other manuscripts \fq City of the Sun\f*
\p
\v 19 In that day there will be an \x + \xo 19:19 \xt [2 Kgs. 5:17] \x*altar to the \nd Lord\nd* in the midst of the land of Egypt, and a \x + \xo 19:19 \xt [Gen. 28:18]\x*pillar to the \nd Lord\nd* at its border.
\v 20 \x + \xo 19:20 \xt [See ver. 19 above] \x*It will be a sign and a witness to the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts in the land of Egypt. When they cry to the \nd Lord\nd* because of oppressors, \x + \xo 19:20 \xt [Obad. 21]\x*he will send them a savior and defender, and deliver them.
\v 21 \x + \xo 19:21 \xt [ver. 25] \x*And the \nd Lord\nd* will make himself known to the Egyptians, and the Egyptians will know the \nd Lord\nd* in that day \x + \xo 19:21 \xt Zech. 14:16-18; [ch. 2:2]\x*and worship with sacrifice and offering, and they will make vows to the \nd Lord\nd* and perform them.
\v 22 \x + \xo 19:22 \xt Jer. 46:25, 26\x*And the \nd Lord\nd* will strike Egypt, striking and healing, and they will return to the \nd Lord\nd*, and he will listen to their pleas for mercy and heal them.
\p
\v 23 \x + \xo 19:23 \xt ch. 11:16 \x*In that day there will be a highway from Egypt to Assyria, and Assyria will come into Egypt, and Egypt into Assyria, \x + \xo 19:23 \xt [ver. 18, 21; Zeph. 3:9]\x*and the Egyptians will worship with the Assyrians.
\p
\v 24 In that day Israel will be the third with Egypt and Assyria, \x + \xo 19:24 \xt [Gen. 12:2, 3]\x*a blessing in the midst of the earth,
\v 25 whom the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts has blessed, saying, “Blessed be Egypt \x + \xo 19:25 \xt [Hos. 2:23] \x*my people, and Assyria \x + \xo 19:25 \xt ch. 29:23 \x*the work of my hands, and \x + \xo 19:25 \xt Deut. 32:9\x*Israel my inheritance.”
\c 20
\s1 A Sign Against Egypt and Cush
\p
\v 1 In the year that \x + \xo 20:1 \xt 2 Kgs. 18:17 \x*the commander in chief, who was sent by Sargon the king of Assyria, came to \x + \xo 20:1 \xt 1 Sam. 5:1\x*Ashdod and fought against it and captured it—
\v 2 at that time the \nd Lord\nd* spoke by Isaiah the son of Amoz, saying, “Go, and loose the sackcloth from your waist and take off your sandals from your feet,” and he did so, walking \x + \xo 20:2 \xt Mic. 1:8, 11; [1 Sam. 19:24]\x*naked and barefoot.
\p
\v 3 Then the \nd Lord\nd* said, “As my servant Isaiah has walked naked and barefoot for three years \x + \xo 20:3 \xt [ch. 8:18]\x*as a sign and a portent against Egypt and Cush,\f + \fr 20:3 \ft Probably \fq Nubia\f*
\v 4 so shall the \x + \xo 20:4 \xt ch. 19:4\x*king of Assyria lead away the Egyptian captives and the Cushite exiles, both the young and the old, naked and barefoot, with buttocks uncovered, the nakedness of Egypt.
\v 5 \x + \xo 20:5 \xt ch. 30:3, 5; [ch. 37:9]\x*Then they shall be dismayed and ashamed because of Cush their hope and of Egypt their boast.
\v 6 And the inhabitants of \x + \xo 20:6 \xt Jer. 47:7; [ch. 14:29, 31] \x*this coastland will say in that day, ‘Behold, this is what has happened to those in whom we hoped and \x + \xo 20:6 \xt [ch. 37:6]\x*to whom we fled for help to be delivered from the king of Assyria! And we, how shall we escape?’”
\c 21
\s1 Fallen, Fallen Is Babylon
\p
\v 1 The \x + \xo 21:1 \xt See ch. 13:1 \x*oracle concerning the wilderness of \x + \xo 21:1 \xt Jer. 51:36, 42 \x*the sea.
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 21:1 \xt Jer. 51:1\x*As whirlwinds in the Negeb sweep on,
\q2 it comes from the wilderness,
\q2 from a terrible land.
\q1
\v 2 A stern vision is told to me;
\q2 \x + \xo 21:2 \xt ch. 24:16; 33:1 \x*the traitor betrays,
\q2 and the destroyer destroys.
\q1 Go up, O \x + \xo 21:2 \xt See ch. 11:11 \x*Elam;
\q2 lay siege, O \x + \xo 21:2 \xt See ch. 13:17 \x*Media;
\q1 all the \x + \xo 21:2 \xt Ezek. 9:4\x*sighing she has caused
\q2 I bring to an end.
\q1
\v 3 Therefore my loins are filled with anguish;
\q2 \x + \xo 21:3 \xt See ch. 13:8\x*pangs have seized me,
\q2 like the pangs of a woman in labor;
\q1 I am bowed down so that I cannot hear;
\q2 I am dismayed so that I cannot see.
\q1
\v 4 My heart staggers; horror has appalled me;
\q2 \x + \xo 21:4 \xt [Deut. 28:67]\x*the twilight I longed for
\q2 has been turned for me into trembling.
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 21:5 \xt Jer. 51:39, 57 \x*They prepare the table,
\q2 they spread the rugs,\f + \fr 21:5 \ft Or \fq they set the watchman\f*
\q2 they eat, they drink.
\q1 Arise, O princes;
\q2 \x + \xo 21:5 \xt 2 Sam. 1:21\x*oil the shield!
\q1
\v 6 For thus the Lord said to me:
\q1 “Go, set a watchman;
\q2 let him announce what he sees.
\q1
\v 7 When he sees riders, horsemen in pairs,
\q2 riders on donkeys, riders on camels,
\q1 let him listen diligently,
\q2 very diligently.”
\q1
\v 8 Then he who saw cried out:\f + \fr 21:8 \ft Dead Sea Scroll, Syriac; Masoretic Text \fq Then a lion cried out\ft , or \fq Then he cried out like a lion\f*
\q1 \x + \xo 21:8 \xt Hab. 2:1\x*“Upon a watchtower I stand, O Lord,
\q2 continually by day,
\q1 and at my post I am stationed
\q2 whole nights.
\q1
\v 9 And behold, here come riders,
\q2 horsemen in pairs!”
\q1 \x + \xo 21:9 \xt [Hab. 2:2] \x*And he answered,
\q2 \x + \xo 21:9 \xt Jer. 51:8; Cited Rev. 14:8; 18:2 \x*“Fallen, fallen is Babylon;
\q1 \x + \xo 21:9 \xt ch. 46:1\x*and all the carved images of her gods
\q2 he has shattered to the ground.”
\q1
\v 10 O \x + \xo 21:10 \xt Jer. 51:33; Amos 1:3; [Mic. 4:13]\x*my threshed and winnowed one,
\q2 what I have heard from the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts,
\q2 the God of Israel, I announce to you.
\b
\p
\v 11 The \x + \xo 21:11 \xt See ch. 13:1 \x*oracle concerning \x + \xo 21:11 \xt Gen. 25:14; 1 Chr. 1:30 \x*Dumah.
\b
\q1 One is calling to me from \x + \xo 21:11 \xt Deut. 2:8; Ezek. 35:2\x*Seir,
\q2 “Watchman, what time of the night?
\q2 Watchman, what time of the night?”
\q1
\v 12 The watchman says:
\q1 “Morning comes, and also \x + \xo 21:12 \xt [Job 36:20; Amos 5:8] \x*the night.
\q2 If you will inquire, \x + \xo 21:12 \xt [Ps. 37:36]\x*inquire;
\q2 come back again.”
\b
\p
\v 13 The \x + \xo 21:13 \xt See ch. 13:1 \x*oracle concerning \x + \xo 21:13 \xt Gen. 25:3; Jer. 25:23, 24 \x*Arabia.
\b
\q1 In the thickets in \x + \xo 21:13 \xt Gen. 25:3; Jer. 25:23, 24 \x*Arabia you will lodge,
\q2 O \x + \xo 21:13 \xt [Gen. 37:25]\x*caravans of \x + \xo 21:13 \xt Gen. 25:3; Jer. 25:23, 24 \x*Dedanites.
\q1
\v 14 To the thirsty bring water;
\q2 meet the fugitive with bread,
\q2 O inhabitants of the land of \x + \xo 21:14 \xt Job 6:19\x*Tema.
\q1
\v 15 For they have fled from the swords,
\q2 from the drawn sword,
\q1 from the bent bow,
\q2 and from the press of battle.
\b
\p
\v 16 For thus the Lord said to me, “Within a year, \x + \xo 21:16 \xt See ch. 16:14 \x*according to the years of a hired worker, all the glory of \x + \xo 21:16 \xt ch. 60:7; Gen. 25:13; Ps. 120:5, 6; Song 1:5; Jer. 2:10; 49:28; Ezek. 27:21\x*Kedar will come to an end.
\v 17 And the remainder of the archers of the mighty men of the sons of \x + \xo 21:17 \xt [See ver. 16 above] \x*Kedar will be few, \x + \xo 21:17 \xt ch. 1:20\x*for the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel, has spoken.”
\c 22
\s1 An Oracle Concerning Jerusalem
\p
\v 1 The \x + \xo 22:1 \xt See ch. 13:1 \x*oracle concerning \x + \xo 22:1 \xt ver. 5; Jer. 21:13; [Joel 3:12, 14]\x*the valley of vision.
\b
\q1 What do you mean that you have gone up,
\q2 all of you, to the housetops,
\q1
\v 2 you who are full of shoutings,
\q2 tumultuous city, \x + \xo 22:2 \xt ch. 32:13 \x*exultant town?
\q1 Your slain are \x + \xo 22:2 \xt Lam. 4:9\x*not slain with the sword
\q2 or dead in battle.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 22:3 \xt [ch. 1:10]\x*All your leaders have fled together;
\q2 without the bow they were captured.
\q1 All of you who were found were captured,
\q2 though they had fled far away.
\q1
\v 4 Therefore I said:
\q1 “Look away from me;
\q2 \x + \xo 22:4 \xt Jer. 9:1; Mic. 1:8\x*let me weep bitter tears;
\q1 do not labor to comfort me
\q2 concerning the destruction of the daughter of my people.”
\b
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 22:5 \xt ch. 2:12-17 \x*For the Lord \nd God\nd* of hosts has \x + \xo 22:5 \xt [ch. 37:3] \x*a day
\q2 of tumult and \x + \xo 22:5 \xt ch. 10:6; 18:2 \x*trampling and \x + \xo 22:5 \xt Mic. 7:4 \x*confusion
\q2 in \x + \xo 22:5 \xt [See ver. 1 above]\x*the valley of vision,
\q1 a battering down of walls
\q2 and a shouting to the mountains.
\q1
\v 6 And \x + \xo 22:6 \xt See ch. 11:11 \x*Elam bore the quiver
\q2 with chariots and horsemen,
\q2 and \x + \xo 22:6 \xt 2 Kgs. 16:9\x*Kir uncovered the shield.
\q1
\v 7 Your choicest valleys were full of chariots,
\q2 and the horsemen took their stand at the gates.
\q1
\v 8 He has taken away \x + \xo 22:8 \xt ch. 30:1 \x*the covering of Judah.
\b
\p In that day you looked to \x + \xo 22:8 \xt 1 Kgs. 10:17\x*the weapons of the House of the Forest,
\v 9 and you saw that \x + \xo 22:9 \xt ver. 5, 10; [2 Chr. 32:5] \x*the breaches of the city of David were many. \x + \xo 22:9 \xt [Neh. 3:16]\x*You collected the waters of the lower pool,
\v 10 and you counted the houses of Jerusalem, and you broke down the houses to fortify the wall.
\v 11 \x + \xo 22:11 \xt [See ver. 9 above] \x*You made a reservoir between \x + \xo 22:11 \xt [2 Kgs. 25:4] \x*the two walls for the water of \x + \xo 22:11 \xt [ch. 7:3; 2 Kgs. 20:20; 2 Chr. 32:3, 4] \x*the old pool. But \x + \xo 22:11 \xt [ch. 5:12]\x*you did not look to him who did it, or see him who planned it long ago.
\b
\q1
\v 12 In that day \x + \xo 22:12 \xt [Joel 2:17] \x*the Lord \nd God\nd* of hosts
\q2 called for weeping and mourning,
\q2 for \x + \xo 22:12 \xt See ch. 3:24 \x*baldness and \x + \xo 22:12 \xt See 2 Sam. 3:31\x*wearing sackcloth;
\q1
\v 13 and behold, joy and gladness,
\q2 killing oxen and slaughtering sheep,
\q2 eating flesh and drinking wine.
\q1 \x + \xo 22:13 \xt ch. 56:12; Cited 1 Cor. 15:32\x*“Let us eat and drink,
\q2 for tomorrow we die.”
\q1
\v 14 The \nd Lord\nd* of hosts \x + \xo 22:14 \xt ch. 5:9 \x*has revealed himself in my ears:
\q1 “Surely \x + \xo 22:14 \xt [ch. 27:9; 1 Sam. 3:14] \x*this iniquity will not be atoned for you \x + \xo 22:14 \xt [ver. 13]\x*until you die,”
\q2 says the Lord \nd God\nd* of hosts.
\b
\p
\v 15 Thus says the Lord \nd God\nd* of hosts, “Come, go to this steward, to \x + \xo 22:15 \xt ch. 36:3, 11, 22; 37:2; 2 Kgs. 18:18, 26, 37; 19:2\x*Shebna, who is over the household, and say to him:
\v 16 What have you to do here, and whom have you here, \x + \xo 22:16 \xt 2 Chr. 16:14 \x*that you have cut out here a tomb for yourself, you \x + \xo 22:16 \xt Matt. 27:60\x*who cut out a tomb on the height and carve a dwelling for yourself in the rock?
\v 17 Behold, the \nd Lord\nd* will hurl you away violently, O you strong man. \x + \xo 22:17 \xt [Dan. 3:21]\x*He will seize firm hold on you
\v 18 and whirl you around and around, and throw you like a ball into a wide land. There you shall die, and there shall be \x + \xo 22:18 \xt [ch. 36:9]\x*your glorious chariots, you shame of your master’s house.
\v 19 \x + \xo 22:19 \xt [ver. 25]\x*I will thrust you from your office, and you will be pulled down from your station.
\v 20 In that day I will call my servant \x + \xo 22:20 \xt ch. 36:3; 37:2; 2 Kgs. 18:18, 26, 37; 19:2\x*Eliakim the son of Hilkiah,
\v 21 and \x + \xo 22:21 \xt [See ver. 20 above] \x*I will clothe him with your robe, and will bind your sash on him, and will commit your authority to his hand. And he shall be \x + \xo 22:21 \xt Gen. 45:8\x*a father to the inhabitants of Jerusalem and to the house of Judah.
\v 22 And I will place \x + \xo 22:22 \xt ch. 9:6 \x*on his shoulder \x + \xo 22:22 \xt Rev. 3:7 \x*the key of the house of David. \x + \xo 22:22 \xt [Job 12:14]\x*He shall open, and none shall shut; and he shall shut, and none shall open.
\v 23 And I will fasten him \x + \xo 22:23 \xt [ch. 33:20; 54:2; Eccles. 12:11] \x*like a peg in a secure place, and he will become \x + \xo 22:23 \xt [Rev. 3:21]\x*a throne of honor to his father’s house.
\v 24 And they will hang on him the whole honor of his father’s house, the offspring and issue, every small vessel, from the cups to all the flagons.
\v 25 In that day, declares the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts, \x + \xo 22:25 \xt [See ver. 23 above]\x*the peg that was fastened in a secure place will give way, and it will be cut down and fall, and the load that was on it will be cut off, for the \nd Lord\nd* has spoken.”
\c 23
\s1 An Oracle Concerning Tyre and Sidon
\p
\v 1 The \x + \xo 23:1 \xt See ch. 13:1 \x*oracle concerning \x + \xo 23:1 \xt [Jer. 25:22; 27:2, 3]; See Ezek. 26:2–28:24; Joel 3:4-8; Amos 1:9, 10; Zech. 9:2-4 \x*Tyre.
\b
\q1 Wail, O \x + \xo 23:1 \xt ver. 14; 1 Kgs. 10:22; 22:48 \x*ships of Tarshish,
\q2 for Tyre is laid waste, \x + \xo 23:1 \xt ch. 24:10 \x*without house or harbor!
\q1 From \x + \xo 23:1 \xt Jer. 2:10; See Gen. 10:4\x*the land of Cyprus\f + \fr 23:1 \ft Hebrew \fq Kittim\ft ; also verse 12\f*
\q2 it is revealed to them.
\q1
\v 2 Be still, O inhabitants of the coast;
\q2 the merchants of \x + \xo 23:2 \xt ver. 4, 12; Gen. 10:15; Josh. 19:28; Jer. 25:22; 27:3; Ezek. 27:8; 32:30; Joel 3:4; Zech. 9:2\x*Sidon, who cross the sea, have filled you.
\q1
\v 3 And on many waters
\q1 your revenue was the grain of Shihor,
\q2 the harvest of the Nile;
\q2 you were \x + \xo 23:3 \xt See Ezek. 27:3-23\x*the merchant of the nations.
\q1
\v 4 Be ashamed, O \x + \xo 23:4 \xt [See ver. 2 above]\x*Sidon, for the sea has spoken,
\q2 the stronghold of the sea, saying:
\q1 “I have neither labored nor given birth,
\q2 I have neither reared young men
\q2 nor brought up young women.”
\q1
\v 5 When the report comes to Egypt,
\q2 they will be in anguish\f + \fr 23:5 \ft Hebrew \fq they will have labor pains\f* over the report about Tyre.
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 23:6 \xt ver. 12\x*Cross over to Tarshish;
\q2 wail, O inhabitants of the coast!
\q1
\v 7 Is this your exultant city
\q2 \x + \xo 23:7 \xt [Gen. 10:15]\x*whose origin is from days of old,
\q1 whose feet carried her
\q2 to settle far away?
\q1
\v 8 Who has purposed this
\q2 against Tyre, the bestower of crowns,
\q1 whose merchants were princes,
\q2 whose traders were the honored of the earth?
\q1
\v 9 The \nd Lord\nd* of hosts has purposed it,
\q2 \x + \xo 23:9 \xt [Ezek. 28:7]\x*to defile the pompous pride of all glory,\f + \fr 23:9 \ft The Hebrew words for \fq glory \ft and \fq hosts \ft sound alike\f*
\q2 to dishonor all the honored of the earth.
\q1
\v 10 Cross over your land like the Nile,
\q2 O daughter of Tarshish;
\q2 there is no restraint anymore.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 23:11 \xt [Ex. 14:21]\x*He has stretched out his hand over the sea;
\q2 he has shaken the kingdoms;
\q1 the \nd Lord\nd* has given command concerning Canaan
\q2 to destroy its strongholds.
\q1
\v 12 And he said:
\q1 “You will no more exult,
\q2 O oppressed virgin daughter of \x + \xo 23:12 \xt See ver. 2 \x*Sidon;
\q1 arise, \x + \xo 23:12 \xt ver. 6 \x*cross over to \x + \xo 23:12 \xt ver. 1\x*Cyprus,
\q2 even there you will have no rest.”
\b
\p
\v 13 Behold the land of \x + \xo 23:13 \xt ch. 47:1; 48:14 \x*the Chaldeans! This is the people that was not;\f + \fr 23:13 \ft Or \fq that has become nothing\f* Assyria destined it for wild beasts. They erected \x + \xo 23:13 \xt [2 Kgs. 25:1]\x*their siege towers, they stripped her palaces bare, they made her a ruin.
\b
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 23:14 \xt See ver. 1\x*Wail, O ships of Tarshish,
\q2 for your stronghold is laid waste.
\b
\m
\v 15 In that day Tyre will be forgotten for \x + \xo 23:15 \xt Jer. 25:11, 22\x*seventy years, like the days\f + \fr 23:15 \ft Or \fq lifetime\f* of one king. At the end of \x + \xo 23:15 \xt Jer. 25:11, 22\x*seventy years, it will happen to Tyre as in the song of the prostitute:
\b
\q1
\v 16 “Take a harp;
\q2 go about the city,
\q2 O forgotten prostitute!
\q1 Make sweet melody;
\q2 sing many songs,
\q2 that you may be remembered.”
\b
\m
\v 17 At the end of \x + \xo 23:17 \xt Jer. 25:11, 22 \x*seventy years, the \nd Lord\nd* will visit Tyre, and she will return to her wages and \x + \xo 23:17 \xt Rev. 17:1, 2\x*will prostitute herself with all the kingdoms of the world on the face of the earth.
\v 18 Her merchandise and her wages will be holy to the \nd Lord\nd*. It will not be stored or hoarded, but her merchandise will supply abundant food and fine clothing for those who dwell before the \nd Lord\nd*.
\c 24
\s1 Judgment on the Whole Earth
\q1
\v 1 Behold, \x + \xo 24:1 \xt ch. 13:9\x*the \nd Lord\nd* will empty the earth\f + \fr 24:1 \ft Or \fq land\ft ; also throughout this chapter\f* and make it desolate,
\q2 and he will twist its surface and scatter its inhabitants.
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 24:2 \xt Hos. 4:9; [Lam. 4:16]; See ch. 3:1-3 \x*And it shall be, as with the people, so with the priest;
\q2 as with the slave, so with his master;
\q2 as with the maid, so with her mistress;
\q1 \x + \xo 24:2 \xt [Ezek. 7:12, 13] \x*as with the buyer, so with the seller;
\q2 as with the lender, so with the borrower;
\q2 \x + \xo 24:2 \xt [Jer. 15:10]\x*as with the creditor, so with the debtor.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 24:3 \xt ver. 1, 6 \x*The earth shall be utterly empty and utterly plundered;
\q2 \x + \xo 24:3 \xt See ch. 1:20\x*for the \nd Lord\nd* has spoken this word.
\b
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 24:4 \xt [ch. 16:8; Hos. 4:3]\x*The earth mourns and withers;
\q2 the world languishes and withers;
\q2 the highest people of the earth languish.
\q1
\v 5 The earth lies \x + \xo 24:5 \xt Num. 35:33 \x*defiled
\q2 under its inhabitants;
\q1 for \x + \xo 24:5 \xt [ch. 2:6, 8]\x*they have transgressed the laws,
\q2 violated the statutes,
\q2 broken the everlasting covenant.
\q1
\v 6 Therefore \x + \xo 24:6 \xt Zech. 5:3, 4 \x*a curse devours the earth,
\q2 and its inhabitants \x + \xo 24:6 \xt [Ps. 5:10]\x*suffer for their guilt;
\q1 therefore the inhabitants of the earth are scorched,
\q2 and few men are left.
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 24:7 \xt [Joel 1:10, 12]\x*The wine mourns,
\q2 the vine languishes,
\q2 all the merry-hearted sigh.
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 24:8 \xt Jer. 7:34; Hos. 2:11; [Amos 8:10]\x*The mirth of the tambourines is stilled,
\q2 the noise of the jubilant has ceased,
\q2 the mirth of the lyre is stilled.
\q1
\v 9 No more do they drink wine \x + \xo 24:9 \xt [Amos 6:5, 6]\x*with singing;
\q2 strong drink is bitter to those who drink it.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 24:10 \xt [ch. 34:11] \x*The wasted city is broken down;
\q2 \x + \xo 24:10 \xt ch. 23:1\x*every house is shut up so that none can enter.
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 24:11 \xt [ver. 7; Ps. 144:14; Joel 1:5] \x*There is an outcry in the streets for lack of wine;
\q2 \x + \xo 24:11 \xt [Joel 1:12]\x*all joy has grown dark;
\q2 the gladness of the earth is banished.
\q1
\v 12 Desolation is left in the city;
\q2 the gates are battered into ruins.
\q1
\v 13 For thus it shall be in the midst of the earth
\q2 among the nations,
\q1 \x + \xo 24:13 \xt ch. 17:6; [Mic. 7:1]\x*as when an olive tree is beaten,
\q2 as at the gleaning when the grape harvest is done.
\b
\q1
\v 14 They lift up their voices, they sing for joy;
\q2 over the majesty of the \nd Lord\nd* they shout from the west.\f + \fr 24:14 \ft Hebrew \fq from the sea\f*
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 24:15 \xt [ch. 45:6]\x*Therefore in the east\f + \fr 24:15 \ft Hebrew \fq in the realm of light\f* give glory to the \nd Lord\nd*;
\q2 in the coastlands of the sea, give glory to the name of the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of Israel.
\q1
\v 16 \x + \xo 24:16 \xt [ver. 14] \x*From the ends of the earth we hear songs of praise,
\q2 of glory to \x + \xo 24:16 \xt [ch. 26:2; 60:21] \x*the Righteous One.
\q1 But I say, “I waste away,
\q2 I waste away. Woe is me!
\q1 For \x + \xo 24:16 \xt ch. 21:2; 33:1\x*the traitors have betrayed,
\q2 with betrayal the traitors have betrayed.”
\b
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 24:17 \xt Jer. 48:43, 44; [Job 20:24; Amos 5:19]\x*Terror and the pit and the snare\f + \fr 24:17 \ft The Hebrew words for \fq terror\ft , \fq pit\ft , and \fq snare \ft sound alike\f*
\q2 are upon you, O inhabitant of the earth!
\q1
\v 18 \x + \xo 24:18 \xt [See ver. 17 above] \x*He who flees at the sound of the terror
\q2 shall fall into the pit,
\q1 and he who climbs out of the pit
\q2 shall be caught in the snare.
\q1 For \x + \xo 24:18 \xt See Gen. 7:11 \x*the windows of heaven are opened,
\q2 and \x + \xo 24:18 \xt Ps. 18:7\x*the foundations of the earth tremble.
\q1
\v 19 The earth is utterly broken,
\q2 the earth is split apart,
\q2 the earth is violently shaken.
\q1
\v 20 The earth \x + \xo 24:20 \xt [ch. 19:14; 29:9] \x*staggers like a drunken man;
\q2 it sways like a hut;
\q1 \x + \xo 24:20 \xt [ver. 5, 6]\x*its transgression lies heavy upon it,
\q2 and it falls, and will not rise again.
\b
\q1
\v 21 On that day the \nd Lord\nd* will punish
\q2 the host of heaven, in heaven,
\q2 and \x + \xo 24:21 \xt Ps. 76:12; [ch. 10:12; 31:8]\x*the kings of the earth, on the earth.
\q1
\v 22 \x + \xo 24:22 \xt Mic. 4:11, 12 \x*They will be gathered together
\q2 as prisoners in a pit;
\q1 they will be shut up in a prison,
\q2 and after many days \x + \xo 24:22 \xt ch. 29:6\x*they will be punished.
\q1
\v 23 \x + \xo 24:23 \xt See ch. 13:10 \x*Then the moon will be confounded
\q2 and the sun ashamed,
\q1 for \x + \xo 24:23 \xt Ps. 99:1, 2; Mic. 4:7\x*the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts reigns
\q2 on Mount Zion and in Jerusalem,
\q1 and his glory will be before his elders.
\c 25
\s1 God Will Swallow Up Death Forever
\q1
\v 1 O \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 25:1 \xt Ex. 15:2 \x*you are my God;
\q2 \x + \xo 25:1 \xt [Ps. 107:32] \x*I will exalt you; I will praise your name,
\q1 for you have done wonderful things,
\q2 \x + \xo 25:1 \xt [2 Kgs. 19:25]\x*plans formed of old, faithful and sure.
\q1
\v 2 For you have made the city \x + \xo 25:2 \xt [ch. 17:1; Jer. 51:37]\x*a heap,
\q2 the fortified city a ruin;
\q1 the foreigners’ palace is a city no more;
\q2 it will never be rebuilt.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 25:3 \xt [ch. 18:7]\x*Therefore strong peoples will glorify you;
\q2 cities of ruthless nations will fear you.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 25:4 \xt Nah. 1:7 \x*For you have been a stronghold to the poor,
\q2 a stronghold to the needy in his distress,
\q2 \x + \xo 25:4 \xt ch. 4:6 \x*a shelter from the storm and a shade from the heat;
\q1 \x + \xo 25:4 \xt [2 Chr. 32:18]\x*for the breath of the ruthless is like a storm against a wall,
\q2
\v 5 \x + \xo 25:5 \xt [ch. 32:2]\x*like heat in a dry place.
\q1 You subdue the noise of the foreigners;
\q2 as heat by the shade of a cloud,
\q2 so the song of the ruthless is put down.
\b
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 25:6 \xt ch. 2:2, 3; 11:9; 24:23 \x*On this mountain the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts will make for all peoples
\q2 a feast of rich food, a feast of well-aged wine,
\q2 \x + \xo 25:6 \xt [Ps. 63:5]\x*of rich food full of marrow, of aged wine well refined.
\q1
\v 7 And he will swallow up \x + \xo 25:7 \xt [See ver. 6 above] \x*on this mountain
\q2 the covering that is cast over all peoples,
\q2 \x + \xo 25:7 \xt [2 Cor. 3:15]\x*the veil that is spread over all nations.
\q2
\v 8 \x + \xo 25:8 \xt Cited 1 Cor. 15:54; [Hos. 13:14] \x*He will swallow up death forever;
\q1 and \x + \xo 25:8 \xt Rev. 7:17; [ch. 30:19] \x*the Lord \nd God\nd* will wipe away tears from all faces,
\q2 and \x + \xo 25:8 \xt [ch. 37:4] \x*the reproach of his people he will take away from all the earth,
\q2 \x + \xo 25:8 \xt See ch. 1:20\x*for the \nd Lord\nd* has spoken.
\q1
\v 9 It will be said on that day,
\q2 “Behold, this is our God; \x + \xo 25:9 \xt ch. 26:8; [Gen. 49:18; Ps. 27:14] \x*we have waited for him, that he might save us.
\q2 This is the \nd Lord\nd*; we have waited for him;
\q2 \x + \xo 25:9 \xt Ps. 9:14\x*let us be glad and rejoice in his salvation.”
\q1
\v 10 For the hand of the \nd Lord\nd* will rest \x + \xo 25:10 \xt [See ver. 6 above] \x*on this mountain,
\q2 and \x + \xo 25:10 \xt See ch. 15:1\x*Moab shall be trampled down in his place,
\q2 as straw is trampled down in a dunghill.\f + \fr 25:10 \ft The Hebrew words for \fq dunghill \ft and for the Moabite town \fq Madmen \ft (Jeremiah 48:2) sound alike\f*
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 25:11 \xt [ch. 16:12] \x*And he will spread out his hands in the midst of it
\q2 as a swimmer spreads his hands out to swim,
\q2 but the \nd Lord\nd* \x + \xo 25:11 \xt [ch. 16:14]\x*will lay low his pompous pride together with the skill\f + \fr 25:11 \ft Or \fq in spite of the skill\f* of his hands.
\q1
\v 12 And the high fortifications of his walls he will bring down,
\q2 lay low, and cast to the ground, to the dust.
\c 26
\s1 You Keep Him in Perfect Peace
\p
\v 1 In that day \x + \xo 26:1 \xt [ch. 27:2] \x*this song will be sung in the land of Judah:
\b
\q1 “We have a strong city;
\q2 he sets up \x + \xo 26:1 \xt [ch. 60:18]\x*salvation
\q2 as walls and bulwarks.
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 26:2 \xt Ps. 118:19, 20\x*Open the gates,
\q2 that the righteous nation that keeps faith may enter in.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 26:3 \xt [ch. 30:15]\x*You keep him in perfect peace
\q2 whose mind is stayed on you,
\q2 because he trusts in you.
\q1
\v 4 Trust in the \nd Lord\nd* forever,
\q2 for the \nd Lord\nd* \nd God\nd* is an everlasting rock.
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 26:5 \xt ch. 25:12\x*For he has humbled
\q2 the inhabitants of the height,
\q2 the lofty city.
\q1 He lays it low, lays it low to the ground,
\q2 casts it to the dust.
\q1
\v 6 The foot tramples it,
\q2 the feet of \x + \xo 26:6 \xt [ch. 25:4]\x*the poor,
\q2 the steps of \x + \xo 26:6 \xt [ch. 25:4]\x*the needy.”
\b
\q1
\v 7 The path of the righteous is level;
\q2 \x + \xo 26:7 \xt 1 Sam. 2:9; Ps. 37:23\x*you make level the way of the righteous.
\q1
\v 8 In the path of your judgments,
\q2 O \nd Lord\nd*, we wait for you;
\q1 \x + \xo 26:8 \xt Ex. 3:15\x*your name and \x + \xo 26:8 \xt Ex. 3:15\x*remembrance
\q2 are the desire of our soul.
\q1
\v 9 My soul yearns for you in the night;
\q2 my spirit within me earnestly seeks you.
\q1 \x + \xo 26:9 \xt ver. 16; [2 Chr. 33:12]\x*For when your judgments are in the earth,
\q2 the inhabitants of the world learn righteousness.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 26:10 \xt See Ps. 73:3-11\x*If favor is shown to the wicked,
\q2 he does not learn righteousness;
\q1 in the land of uprightness he deals corruptly
\q2 and does not see the majesty of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 11 O \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 26:11 \xt [Mic. 5:9] \x*your hand is lifted up,
\q2 but \x + \xo 26:11 \xt [ch. 5:12] \x*they do not see it.
\q1 Let them see your zeal for your people, and be ashamed.
\q2 Let \x + \xo 26:11 \xt Ps. 21:9; [ch. 33:14]\x*the fire for your adversaries consume them.
\q1
\v 12 O \nd Lord\nd*, you will ordain \x + \xo 26:12 \xt ch. 9:7; Mic. 5:5\x*peace for us,
\q2 for you have indeed done for us all our works.
\q1
\v 13 O \nd Lord\nd* our God,
\q2 \x + \xo 26:13 \xt [ch. 2:8; 2 Kgs. 16:3, 4] \x*other lords besides you have ruled over us,
\q2 \x + \xo 26:13 \xt [ch. 2:20; Ps. 20:7]; See 2 Kgs. 18:4-6\x*but your name alone we bring to remembrance.
\q1
\v 14 They are dead, they will not live;
\q2 they are shades, they will not arise;
\q1 to that end you have visited them with destruction
\q2 and wiped out all remembrance of them.
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 26:15 \xt ch. 9:3 \x*But you have increased the nation, O \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 you have increased the nation; you are glorified;
\q2 \x + \xo 26:15 \xt [ch. 54:2, 3]\x*you have enlarged all the borders of the land.
\b
\q1
\v 16 O \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 26:16 \xt Hos. 5:15; See ch. 37:1-4\x*in distress they sought you;
\q2 they poured out a whispered prayer
\q2 when your discipline was upon them.
\q1
\v 17 \x + \xo 26:17 \xt See ch. 13:8\x*Like a pregnant woman
\q2 who writhes and cries out in her pangs
\q2 when she is near to giving birth,
\q1 so were we because of you, O \nd Lord\nd*;
\q2
\v 18 \x + \xo 26:18 \xt [See ver. 17 above]\x*we were pregnant, we writhed,
\q2 but we have given birth to wind.
\q1 We have accomplished no deliverance in the earth,
\q2 and the inhabitants of the world have not fallen.
\q1
\v 19 \x + \xo 26:19 \xt [Ezek. 37:12; Dan. 12:2; Hos. 13:14] \x*Your dead shall live; their bodies shall rise.
\q2 You who dwell in the dust, awake and sing for joy!
\q1 For \x + \xo 26:19 \xt [Hos. 14:5]\x*your dew is a dew of light,
\q2 and the earth will give birth to the dead.
\b
\q1
\v 20 Come, my people, enter your chambers,
\q2 and shut your doors behind you;
\q1 hide yourselves \x + \xo 26:20 \xt ch. 10:25\x*for a little while
\q2 until the fury has passed by.
\q1
\v 21 \x + \xo 26:21 \xt Mic. 1:3 \x*For behold, the \nd Lord\nd* is coming out from his place
\q2 to punish the inhabitants of \x + \xo 26:21 \xt [ch. 24:5]\x*the earth for their iniquity,
\q1 and the earth will disclose the blood shed on it,
\q2 and will no more cover its slain.
\c 27
\s1 The Redemption of Israel
\p
\v 1 In that day the \nd Lord\nd* with his hard and great and strong \x + \xo 27:1 \xt [Jer. 47:6] \x*sword will punish \x + \xo 27:1 \xt Ps. 74:14 \x*Leviathan the fleeing serpent, \x + \xo 27:1 \xt Ps. 74:14 \x*Leviathan the twisting serpent, and he will slay \x + \xo 27:1 \xt ch. 51:9; Ezek. 29:3\x*the dragon that is in the sea.
\b
\q1
\v 2 In that day,
\q1 \x + \xo 27:2 \xt ch. 5:7 \x*“A pleasant vineyard,\f + \fr 27:2 \ft Many Hebrew manuscripts \fq A vineyard of wine\f* \x + \xo 27:2 \xt [ch. 26:1]\x*sing of it!
\q2
\v 3 I, the \nd Lord\nd*, am its keeper;
\q2 every moment I water it.
\q2 Lest anyone punish it,
\q1 I keep it night and day;
\q2
\v 4 I have no wrath.
\q1 \x + \xo 27:4 \xt [ch. 10:17]\x*Would that I had thorns and briers to battle!
\q2 I would march against them,
\q2 I would burn them up together.
\q1
\v 5 Or let them lay hold of my protection,
\q2 let them make peace with me,
\q2 let them make peace with me.”
\b
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 27:6 \xt ch. 37:31; Hos. 14:5, 6\x*In days to come\f + \fr 27:6 \ft Hebrew \fq In those to come\f* Jacob shall take root,
\q2 Israel shall blossom and put forth shoots
\q2 and fill the whole world with fruit.
\b
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 27:7 \xt Hos. 6:1, 2 \x*Has he struck them \x + \xo 27:7 \xt See ch. 37:36-38 \x*as he struck those who struck them?
\q2 Or have they been slain \x + \xo 27:7 \xt ch. 37:18, 19\x*as their slayers were slain?
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 27:8 \xt [Jer. 10:24] \x*Measure by measure,\f + \fr 27:8 \ft Or \fq By driving her away\ft ; the meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain\f* by exile you contended with them;
\q2 \x + \xo 27:8 \xt [Jer. 18:17]\x*he removed them with his fierce breath\f + \fr 27:8 \ft Or \fq wind\f* in the day of the east wind.
\q1
\v 9 Therefore by this \x + \xo 27:9 \xt [ch. 22:14] \x*the guilt of Jacob will be atoned for,
\q2 and this will be the full fruit of the removal of his sin:\f + \fr 27:9 \ft Septuagint \fq and this is the blessing when I take away his sin\f*
\q1 \x + \xo 27:9 \xt [2 Kgs. 18:4] \x*when he makes all the stones of the altars
\q2 like chalkstones crushed to pieces,
\q2 no \x + \xo 27:9 \xt See Deut. 16:21\x*Asherim or incense altars will remain standing.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 27:10 \xt ch. 17:9; 32:14, 19; [Hos. 8:14; Mic. 5:11]\x*For the fortified city is solitary,
\q2 a habitation deserted and forsaken, like the wilderness;
\q1 there the calf grazes;
\q2 there it lies down and strips its branches.
\q1
\v 11 When its boughs are dry, they are broken;
\q2 women come and make a fire of them.
\q1 \x + \xo 27:11 \xt Deut. 32:28; See ch. 30:16-18\x*For this is a people without discernment;
\q2 therefore he who made them will not have compassion on them;
\q2 he who formed them will show them no favor.
\b
\p
\v 12 In that day \x + \xo 27:12 \xt See Gen. 15:18\x*from the river Euphrates\f + \fr 27:12 \ft Hebrew \fq from the River\f* to the Brook of Egypt the \nd Lord\nd* will thresh out the grain, and you will be gleaned one by one, O people of Israel.
\v 13 And in that day \x + \xo 27:13 \xt Lev. 25:9; [Matt. 24:31; Rev. 11:15] \x*a great trumpet will be blown, \x + \xo 27:13 \xt ch. 11:11, 16; Mic. 7:12 \x*and those who were lost in the land of Assyria and those who were driven out to the land of Egypt \x + \xo 27:13 \xt [ch. 2:2]\x*will come and worship the \nd Lord\nd* on the holy mountain at Jerusalem.
\c 28
\s1 Judgment on Ephraim and Jerusalem
\q1
\v 1 Ah, the proud crown of \x + \xo 28:1 \xt [Hos. 7:5]\x*the drunkards of Ephraim,
\q2 and the fading flower of its glorious beauty,
\q2 which is on the head of the rich valley of those overcome with wine!
\q1
\v 2 Behold, the Lord has \x + \xo 28:2 \xt [ch. 8:7] \x*one who is mighty and strong;
\q2 like a storm of hail, a destroying tempest,
\q1 like \x + \xo 28:2 \xt ver. 15, 18\x*a storm of mighty, overflowing waters,
\q2 he casts down to the earth with his hand.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 28:3 \xt ver. 1\x*The proud crown of the drunkards of Ephraim
\q2 will be trodden underfoot;
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 28:4 \xt [Amos 8:1, 2] \x*and the fading flower of its glorious beauty,
\q2 which is on the head of the rich valley,
\q1 will be like \x + \xo 28:4 \xt Hos. 9:10; Mic. 7:1\x*a first-ripe fig before the summer:
\q2 when someone sees it, he swallows it
\q2 as soon as it is in his hand.
\b
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 28:5 \xt ch. 2:11\x*In that day the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts will be a crown of glory,\f + \fr 28:5 \ft The Hebrew words for \fq glory \ft and \fq hosts \ft sound alike\f*
\q2 and a diadem of beauty, to the remnant of his people,
\q1
\v 6 and \x + \xo 28:6 \xt [1 Kgs. 3:28] \x*a spirit of justice to him who sits in judgment,
\q2 and \x + \xo 28:6 \xt [ch. 38:6]\x*strength to those who turn back the battle at the gate.
\b
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 28:7 \xt [ch. 3:12] \x*These also reel with wine
\q2 and \x + \xo 28:7 \xt Hos. 4:11 \x*stagger with strong drink;
\q1 the priest and \x + \xo 28:7 \xt ch. 9:15; 56:10, 12\x*the prophet reel with strong drink,
\q2 they are swallowed by\f + \fr 28:7 \ft Or \fq confused by\f* wine,
\q2 they stagger with strong drink,
\q1 they reel in vision,
\q2 they stumble in giving judgment.
\q1
\v 8 For all tables are full of filthy vomit,
\q2 with no space left.
\b
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 28:9 \xt Jer. 6:10\x*“To whom will he teach knowledge,
\q2 and to whom will he explain the message?
\q1 Those who are weaned from the milk,
\q2 those taken from the breast?
\q1
\v 10 For it is precept upon precept, precept upon precept,
\q2 line upon line, line upon line,
\q2 here a little, there a little.”
\b
\q1
\v 11 \x + \xo 28:11 \xt Cited 1 Cor. 14:21; See ch. 5:26-29\x*For by people of strange lips
\q2 and with a foreign tongue
\q1 the \nd Lord\nd* will speak to this people,
\q2
\v 12 to whom he has said,
\q1 \x + \xo 28:12 \xt ch. 30:15; [Matt. 11:28, 29]\x*“This is rest;
\q2 give rest to the weary;
\q1 and this is repose”;
\q2 yet they would not hear.
\q1
\v 13 And the word of the \nd Lord\nd* will be to them
\q1 precept upon precept, precept upon precept,
\q2 line upon line, line upon line,
\q2 here a little, there a little,
\q1 \x + \xo 28:13 \xt ch. 8:15\x*that they may go, and fall backward,
\q2 and be broken, and snared, and taken.
\s1 A Cornerstone in Zion
\q1
\v 14 Therefore hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*, you \x + \xo 28:14 \xt ver. 22; ch. 29:20\x*scoffers,
\q2 who rule this people in Jerusalem!
\q1
\v 15 Because you have said, “We have made a covenant with death,
\q2 and with Sheol we have an agreement,
\q1 when the \x + \xo 28:15 \xt ver. 2, 18; [ch. 8:7, 8] \x*overwhelming whip passes through
\q2 it will not come to us,
\q1 for we have made \x + \xo 28:15 \xt [Rom. 1:25]\x*lies our refuge,
\q2 and in falsehood we have taken shelter”;
\q1
\v 16 therefore thus says the Lord \nd God\nd*,
\q1 \x + \xo 28:16 \xt Cited Rom. 9:33; 1 Pet. 2:6; [Ps. 118:22; Matt. 21:42; Acts 4:11] \x*“Behold, I am the one who has laid\f + \fr 28:16 \ft Dead Sea Scroll \fq I am laying\f* as a foundation \x + \xo 28:16 \xt ch. 14:32\x*in Zion,
\q2 a stone, a tested stone,
\q1 a precious cornerstone, of a sure foundation:
\q2 ‘Whoever believes will not be in haste.’
\q1
\v 17 And I will make justice \x + \xo 28:17 \xt [2 Kgs. 21:13]\x*the line,
\q2 and righteousness \x + \xo 28:17 \xt [2 Kgs. 21:13]\x*the plumb line;
\q1 and hail will sweep away the refuge of lies,
\q2 and waters will overwhelm the shelter.”
\q1
\v 18 Then \x + \xo 28:18 \xt ver. 15\x*your covenant with death will be annulled,
\q2 and your agreement with Sheol will not stand;
\q1 when the overwhelming scourge passes through,
\q2 you will be beaten down by it.
\q1
\v 19 As often as it passes through it will take you;
\q2 \x + \xo 28:19 \xt [ch. 50:4] \x*for morning by morning it will pass through,
\q2 by day and by night;
\q1 and it will be \x + \xo 28:19 \xt [2 Chr. 32:18]\x*sheer terror to understand the message.
\q1
\v 20 For the bed is too short to stretch oneself on,
\q2 and the covering too narrow to wrap oneself in.
\q1
\v 21 For the \nd Lord\nd* will rise up \x + \xo 28:21 \xt [2 Sam. 5:20; 1 Chr. 14:11] \x*as on Mount Perazim;
\q2 \x + \xo 28:21 \xt See Josh. 10:10-14 \x*as in the Valley of \x + \xo 28:21 \xt 1 Chr. 14:16; See Josh. 9:3\x*Gibeon he will be roused;
\q1 to do his deed—strange is his deed!
\q2 and to work his work—alien is his work!
\q1
\v 22 Now therefore do not \x + \xo 28:22 \xt ver. 14 \x*scoff,
\q2 lest your bonds be made strong;
\q1 for I have heard \x + \xo 28:22 \xt ch. 10:23\x*a decree of destruction
\q2 from the Lord \nd God\nd* of hosts against the whole land.
\b
\q1
\v 23 Give ear, and hear my voice;
\q2 give attention, and hear my speech.
\q1
\v 24 Does he who plows for sowing plow continually?
\q2 Does he continually open and harrow his ground?
\q1
\v 25 \x + \xo 28:25 \xt [ch. 55:10, 11]\x*When he has leveled its surface,
\q2 does he not scatter dill, sow cumin,
\q1 and put in wheat in rows
\q2 and barley in its proper place,
\q2 and emmer\f + \fr 28:25 \ft A type of wheat\f* as the border?
\q1
\v 26 \x + \xo 28:26 \xt [ch. 21:10]\x*For he is rightly instructed;
\q2 his God teaches him.
\b
\q1
\v 27 Dill is not threshed with a threshing sledge,
\q2 nor is a cart wheel rolled over cumin,
\q1 but dill is beaten out with a stick,
\q2 and cumin with a rod.
\q1
\v 28 Does one crush grain for bread?
\q2 No, he does not thresh it forever;\f + \fr 28:28 \ft Or \fq Grain is crushed for bread; he will surely thresh it, but not forever\f*
\q1 when he drives his cart wheel over it
\q2 with his horses, he does not crush it.
\q1
\v 29 This also comes from the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts;
\q2 he is \x + \xo 28:29 \xt Jer. 32:19; [ch. 9:6]\x*wonderful in counsel
\q2 and excellent in wisdom.
\c 29
\s1 The Siege of Jerusalem
\q1
\v 1 Ah, Ariel, Ariel,
\q2 the city \x + \xo 29:1 \xt [2 Sam. 5:9]\x*where David encamped!
\q1 Add year to year;
\q2 let the feasts run their round.
\q1
\v 2 Yet I will distress Ariel,
\q2 and there shall be moaning and lamentation,
\q2 and she shall be to me like an Ariel.\f + \fr 29:2 \fq Ariel \ft could mean \fq lion of God\ft , or \fq hero \ft (2 Samuel 23:20), or \fq altar hearth \ft (Ezekiel 43:15–16)\f*
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 29:3 \xt [2 Kgs. 25:1; Ezek. 4:2] \x*And I will encamp against you all around,
\q2 and will besiege you \x + \xo 29:3 \xt [Ezek. 21:22; 26:8]\x*with towers
\q2 and I will raise siegeworks against you.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 29:4 \xt [ch. 2:11, 12] \x*And you will be brought low; from the earth you shall speak,
\q2 and from the dust your speech will be bowed down;
\q1 your voice shall come from the ground like \x + \xo 29:4 \xt See ch. 8:19\x*the voice of a ghost,
\q2 and from the dust your speech shall whisper.
\b
\q1
\v 5 But the multitude of your foreign foes shall be like \x + \xo 29:5 \xt ch. 17:13; Ps. 18:42 \x*small dust,
\q2 and the multitude of the ruthless like passing chaff.
\q1 \x + \xo 29:5 \xt [ch. 17:14; 37:36; 2 Kgs. 19:35]\x*And in an instant, suddenly,
\q2
\v 6 \x + \xo 29:6 \xt [1 Kgs. 19:11, 12]\x*you will be visited by the \nd Lord\nd* of hosts
\q1 with thunder and with earthquake and great noise,
\q2 with whirlwind and tempest, and the flame of a devouring fire.
\q1
\v 7 And \x + \xo 29:7 \xt [Zech. 12:9]; See Mic. 4:11-13 \x*the multitude of all the nations that fight against Ariel,
\q2 all that fight against her and her stronghold and distress her,
\q2 shall be \x + \xo 29:7 \xt ch. 17:14; [Job 20:8]\x*like a dream, a vision of the night.
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 29:8 \xt [Ps. 73:20; 90:5]\x*As when a hungry man dreams, and behold, he is eating
\q2 and awakes with his hunger not satisfied,
\q1 or as when a thirsty man dreams, and behold, he is drinking
\q2 and awakes faint, with his thirst not quenched,
\q1 so shall the multitude of all the nations be
\q2 that fight against Mount Zion.
\b
\q1
\v 9 Astonish yourselves\f + \fr 29:9 \ft Or \fq Linger awhile\f* and be astonished;
\q2 blind yourselves and be blind!
\q1 Be drunk, but not with wine;
\q2 \x + \xo 29:9 \xt [ch. 19:14; 24:20]\x*stagger, but not with strong drink!
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 29:10 \xt [ch. 6:10; Rom. 11:8]\x*For the \nd Lord\nd* has poured out upon you
\q2 a spirit of deep sleep,
\q1 and has closed your eyes (the prophets),
\q2 and covered your heads (the seers).
\b
\p
\v 11 And the vision of all this has become to you like the words of a book that is \x + \xo 29:11 \xt ch. 8:16; Dan. 12:4\x*sealed. When men give it to one who can read, saying, “Read this,” he says, “I cannot, for it is sealed.”
\v 12 And when they give the book to one who cannot read, saying, “Read this,” he says, “I cannot read.”
\b
\q1
\v 13 And the Lord said:
\q1 “Because \x + \xo 29:13 \xt Cited Matt. 15:8, 9; Mark 7:6, 7; [Ezek. 33:31] \x*this people \x + \xo 29:13 \xt [ch. 1:12; 58:2]\x*draw near with their mouth
\q2 and honor me with their lips,
\q2 while their hearts are far from me,
\q1 and their fear of me is a commandment taught by men,
\q1
\v 14 therefore, behold, \x + \xo 29:14 \xt Hab. 1:5; See ch. 3:1-4 \x*I will again
\q2 do wonderful things with this people,
\q2 with wonder upon wonder;
\q1 and \x + \xo 29:14 \xt Jer. 49:7; Cited 1 Cor. 1:19\x*the wisdom of their wise men shall perish,
\q2 and the discernment of their discerning men shall be hidden.”
\b
\q1
\v 15 Ah, \x + \xo 29:15 \xt [ch. 30:1] \x*you who hide deep from the \nd Lord\nd* your counsel,
\q2 whose deeds are \x + \xo 29:15 \xt Ezek. 8:12\x*in the dark,
\q2 and who say, “Who sees us? Who knows us?”
\q1
\v 16 \x + \xo 29:16 \xt See ch. 10:15\x*You turn things upside down!
\q1 Shall the potter be regarded as the clay,
\q1 that the thing made should say of its maker,
\q2 “He did not make me”;
\q1 or the thing formed say of him who formed it,
\q2 “He has no understanding”?
\b
\q1
\v 17 Is it not yet a very little while
\q2 \x + \xo 29:17 \xt [Ps. 107:33, 35]\x*until Lebanon shall be turned into a fruitful field,
\q2 and the fruitful field shall be regarded as a forest?
\q1
\v 18 In that day \x + \xo 29:18 \xt [ch. 32:3; 35:5; Matt. 11:5] \x*the deaf shall hear
\q2 \x + \xo 29:18 \xt ver. 12 \x*the words of a book,
\q1 and out of their gloom and darkness
\q2 \x + \xo 29:18 \xt [ch. 35:5; Matt. 11:5]\x*the eyes of the blind shall see.
\q1
\v 19 \x + \xo 29:19 \xt ch. 61:1; [ch. 14:32; Zeph. 3:12; Matt. 5:3]\x*The meek shall obtain fresh joy in the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and the poor among mankind shall exult in the Holy One of Israel.
\q1
\v 20 For the ruthless shall come to nothing
\q2 and \x + \xo 29:20 \xt ch. 28:14, 22\x*the scoffer cease,
\q2 and all who watch to do evil shall be cut off,
\q1
\v 21 who by a word make a man out to be an offender,
\q2 and \x + \xo 29:21 \xt Amos 5:10; [Ps. 127:5] \x*lay a snare for him who reproves in the gate,
\q2 and with an empty plea \x + \xo 29:21 \xt Amos 5:12\x*turn aside him who is in the right.
\b
\p
\v 22 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 29:22 \xt [ch. 51:2]\x*who redeemed Abraham, concerning the house of Jacob:
\b
\q1 “Jacob shall no more be ashamed,
\q2 no more shall his face grow pale.
\q1
\v 23 For when he sees his children,
\q2 \x + \xo 29:23 \xt ch. 19:25; 60:21; [Ps. 100:3] \x*the work of my hands, in his midst,
\q2 they will sanctify my name;
\q1 \x + \xo 29:23 \xt ch. 8:13\x*they will sanctify the Holy One of Jacob
\q2 and will stand in awe of the God of Israel.
\q1
\v 24 And those \x + \xo 29:24 \xt [ch. 28:7]\x*who go astray in spirit will come to understanding,
\q2 and those who murmur will accept instruction.”
\c 30
\s1 Do Not Go Down to Egypt
\q1
\v 1 “Ah, \x + \xo 30:1 \xt [ch. 1:2, 4] \x*stubborn children,” declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q1 \x + \xo 30:1 \xt [ch. 29:15] \x*“who carry out a plan, but not mine,
\q1 and who make \x + \xo 30:1 \xt ch. 25:7\x*an alliance,\f + \fr 30:1 \ft Hebrew \fq who weave a web\f* but not of my Spirit,
\q2 that they may add sin to sin;
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 30:2 \xt ch. 31:1; 36:6\x*who set out to go down to Egypt,
\q2 without asking for my direction,
\q1 to take refuge in the protection of Pharaoh
\q2 and to seek shelter in the shadow of Egypt!
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 30:3 \xt [ver. 7; ch. 20:5]\x*Therefore shall the protection of Pharaoh turn to your shame,
\q2 and the shelter in the shadow of Egypt to your humiliation.
\q1
